You should drive the coast down to Uncle Robert's and the new beach, roam the lava a bit, enjoy the beauty. Many nice places to stop and enjoy the coastline for a moment…..
host_about:
Steve and Janelle keep a casual Puna lifestyle and run an 6 acre organic farm while you enjoy your visit to the Big Island.
  Janelle is a chef and can cook for any size group. She prefers to feature the crops from the farm and has many years of experience to draw upon. The farm has a booth locally6 on Wednesday nights at a farmers market where eating dinner is the main feature, along with the great music!
   Our home and cottages are a sanctuary and we strive to love all, serve all.  This is an adventure for many and sometimes the beginning of a journey…….

name: HawaiianJungleHangout
host_about: Since venturing to the Big Island 20 years ago, I've always been drawn to the volcano, warm springs, and rainforest. As a documentary photographer for over two decades, the dozen different microclimates delight in an ever changing offering of surreal landscapes, diversity of character and faces, exotic/colorful fauna, and island politics, gives a profuse array of visual opportunities and is a photographer's paradise. I feel fortunate to have a home located minutes from all my favorite sites and love having the opportunity to share the experience.

name: Lotus Garden /Charming Attic Room in Downtown Hilo
neighborhood_overview:
Hilo is 'retro town' with old weathered buildings and a slower pace of life.
Downtown is 'walkable' due to being 3 blocks long and 3 blocks wide with plenty of grocery shopping and a Farmer's Market close by. In recent years we have seen more small restaurants open up all over town plus studios for massage and yoga.

Enjoy staying one block from Hilo Bay, the Farmer's Market and close to parks, gardens, cafes, restaurants and galleries. Hilo offers diverse cuisines. Japanese, Thai, Mexican, French Crepes and Indian are among some of the choices you will find and most restaurants are affordably priced...
Travelers on a budget could do without a car here if it's a slow paced vacation they are looking for.. You can enjoy the convenience of being in the same block as some great budget cafes and restaurants as well as grocery stores and the Farmer's Market. Some of our guests do choose not to rent a car for a variety of reasons. When making this choice they usua
host_about:
Aloha I'm Megan. Meet Jasper also. We've been working to create a colorful atmosphere for visitors that reflects the beauty of the tropics. Both of us enjoy helping guests feel comfortable so that they can relax and enjoy all the magic of this wet and wild side of the island. 

Hilo could become known as 'the town that time forgot' because it has the flavor of an older, slower Hawaii. In that way we are pretty easy going and relaxed ourselves. We have two guest cottages and a romantic 1 bedroom apartment here at The Lotus Garden. This is a property that features two garden courtyards, stone Buddha statues, a fish pond and an abundance of tropical plants and trees. . The Lotus Garden is reminiscent of the former 'sugar cane plantation days' when houses were clustered together so that there was a sense of community in the way people lived. Here Travelers meet other travelers in passing. Another wonderful feature of The Lotus Garden is that we are right in the center of town. Guests enjoy being a block away from the Farmer's Market and within walking distance of our cafes, restaurants, galleries and even Hilo's own Kava Bar. 

Just ask us. .. we know some great little beach parks close by and some special things to do around Hilo..  

... Our latest creed to live by? "Now is a really good time!" And so it is..

name: Jungalow forest Retreat

name: Cozy Studio Near the Ocean Cliff  Side
neighborhood_overview:
The neighbors and "locals" in Kalapana Sea View as well as the surrounding areas are relaxed, helpful, and friendly. I have found, they will always give excellent tips on the best current things to do in the local area. Don't miss Uncle Robert's at the West end of the road for a unique island experience filled with music, dance, food and local crafts on Wednesday nights.

This neighborhood is the old Hawaiian feel with overgrown trees, birds, coqui frogs and other cute tropical animals roaming the rich and lush landscapes of the east side of the island.

Here is a recent quote from one of our guests:

What a great find! Was looking for a quiet place close to the water and SherylRose's spot definitely fit the needs. Super quiet, well furnished and just the right mix of a short drive to anything you need to sipping coffee on the patio. Stars were fantastic and the cool ocean breeze was fantastic! Hope others find this place as refreshing! Thanks again.
host_about:
Along with trips back and forth to Hawaii from  Northern CA throughout the year. A wanderlust at heart; I'm constantly on the move and have multiple projects going and trying to find time for new adventures. 

I work as a graphic designer and a freelance photographer. I also run my humble multiple unit vacation property in Hawaii. During my non busy days, I spend my time relaxing with family and catching up with friends!
Also finding time to follow my passion through modern painting and anything handmade. A soft heart for animals and mostly enjoy the company of adventure seeking long life friends and a love for laughter. 

Future travel plans are investing more of my adventure time in the Big Island and explore the raw beauty of my second home. 

"The true fruit of travel is perhaps the feeling of being nearly every where at home." ~Freya Stark

Awesome ocean views. Papaaloa Country Store, Bar and Restaurant is just down the road . Great pizza and local style fresh food. Live music 3 nights a week.

Please be aware that depending on rain fall the property is at risk of drought. This can sometimes cause the pond levels to drop making it less scenic for some.

name: Milo #2 Orchard Mini-Cabin for 2
neighborhood_overview: Our location is pristine. Mango Road is a sacred authentic, well preserved landmark to the ancient Hawaiians and so beautiful.
host_about:
Kirpal Meditation and Ecological Center is a half mile from the ocean on the eastern tip of the Big Island of Hawaii, approximately seven miles from the small village of Pahoa. The 10-acre ocean-view property is blessed with average daytime temperatures of 85° F year-round, and 65° F at night, with cool, fragrant trade winds, surrounding tropical flora, including old growth mangoes, nearby swimming, surfing and snorkeling.

This property was once a papaya farm and is now newly planted with bamboo, papaya, palms, banana and many other fruit trees. The octagonal Balinese meditation pavilion is set among shade-trees with an expansive view of the ocean. The island wildlife is all around us – a variety of birds by day and at night there's the pleasant chirping of Coqui frogs – and there are no snakes. Natural wonders include Volcanoes National Park, for lava and crater viewing, volcanically heated warm ponds and steam vents (as outdoor saunas) and other wonders of the lush tropics.

Kmec opened in the summer of 2008 for pre-arranged seasonal meditation retreats and private meditation-vacations on request. Additionally, we would like to extend our welcome to Big Island travelers offering cozy cottages and open air kitchen and bath. We offer daily free meditation instructions and practices at our beautiful Balinese meditation pavillion. Additionally, we offer Yoga and nature tours upon guest's request (donations accepted).

name: "Angel's Nest @ Kehena Beach"
neighborhood_overview: Our neighborhood is small, beautiful, peaceful, quiet and charming, perfect for strolling thru, either on your way to the beach or just for the sake of a stroll thru the neighborhood.  You may enjoy the vine swing on one of your strolls or just the many beautiful flowers and plants.  You may discover one of the lesser known paths to the ocean.  Perhaps you may want to hike to the lava, it's just a few miles down the famous "red road".  At the end of the "red road" you will find Uncle Robert's awa bar, be sure to check out the Wednesday night market at Uncle's, it's the place to be!  Next door to Uncle's is the Kalapana Café, a great place to get something tasty to eat.  Going the other way on the "red road" just a short distance (still in the neighborhood) is the Ramashala Yoga retreat and just a mile or so farther is the Kalani Honua Yoga retreat.  In between those two is "Space" where there is a fabulous farmers market on Saturday.  A few more miles down red road you will find Ahalan
host_about: I love being in nature so living in Hawaii is perfect for me.  I like to spend time with my family, especially my grandchildren!

name: Mango Tree Cottage : Nestled in the Forest
neighborhood_overview: Wailea is a quaint old plantation village of about 12 households. It is a very friendly and warm community where we know each other. Our families know each other. Every Tuesday, we have our community market and we gather to share,sell, and trade food; great food for our bodies and souls.
host_about:
ALOHA & WELCOME,

Thank you very much for viewing our various accommodations. Our accommodations are located along the lush and tropical Hamakua Coast, 15 miles north of Hilo.
I am  Akiko Masuda, a 3rd generation Japanese woman, born in Honolulu in the 40’s, long before freeways, shopping malls, email, Blackberrys, and cell phones. I have been a writer of children's books, student of tai chi, hula, and zen meditation,  I am a storyteller, hostess, housekeeper, and love caring for our gardens and fruit trees with our weedwhacker and leaf blower. I am the president of the WAILEA VILLAGE HISTORIC PRESERVATION COMMUNITY. I have been living in Wailea Village since' 91, and at that time, was the first person  to buy in this quiet, peaceful country village in 35 years.  Please come and discover the peace and kindness here.

host_about:
I’ve been told that I have reserved 50% of my brain's capacity just for information about Hawaii.  I don't know if that's true, but I am passionate about the islands of Hawaii. So pull up a chair and I'll chat you up.

I think that's why I love Molokai so much. Not much has changed.  Molokai is still what Hawaii is supposed to be, you can feel the ALOHA when you are there.

name: Kepuhi Beach Condo with Loft  #2145
neighborhood_overview: KaluaKoi Resort, or Kepuhi Beach Resort, was built at the same time as The Sheraton Resort. Our section of condos were built with full  kitchens, the other half as hotel rooms with a restaurant, conference rooms, etc. The Sheraton has been closed for over 15yrs now but the grounds, pool, parking, etc. are fully maintained and kept up. This gives a very quiet, peaceful complex with endless coves and beaches to explore with very few people. In the condo is binder full of all activities, restaurants, and places to visit on Molokai. There is a small convenient store on premises by the pool that carries food, snacks, souvenirs, swim suits, etc. The closest large grocery store is 5 miles up the hill to the town of Maunaloa.
host_about:
Patrice and Rose, sisters, own the condo together that you would like to rent. We have been going to Molokai for over 20 years and honestly have to say we wish we lived there.  We love the solitude and peacefulness of Molokai, gives us both a break from our separate busy lives in California. 
We have used Airbnb for vacations to Florida and other great places and have always had great accommodations  and stays.
We have made sure that everything we feel is important to a comfortable, non cluttered, clean and well stocked condo is available  to you. We want you to feel like our condo is yours when you stay there, that would make us happy.

name: ☀ Private Garden w/ Ocean Views → Green Sands ☀
neighborhood_overview: A variety of tropical fresh fruits, rolls, bagels, cream cheese, jelly’s, coffee and teas will be stocked in your kitchen for you to enjoy at your leisure. Enjoy breakfast on your private porch. The studio is newly remodeled with carpet, paint, tile floors and granite counters. It comes complete with clean sheets, towels, hand soap, plates, cups and utensils. The kitchen has a large fridge, stove, oven, microwave, toaster and coffee maker. The washer and dryer is a door away from the kitchen as well as a small library with mostly art and island books to explore. There is also a BBQ to use.
host_about: Born and raised in Hawaii and now living in Los Angeles/Hawaii. I enjoy surfing, snowboarding and photography. We are always working on ways to improve so if ever have any questions or comments please message me on Airbnb. Aloha!! Paul

name: “Patti's Aloha Paradise”
neighborhood_overview:
Absolutely Beautiful! You can get lost in the beauty of the tiny parks that have tide pools and still native Hawaiian plants all only a short walk away.
And I will leave the lights on for you! We have no street lights! Beautiful Starry nights.
host_about:
Aloha, 
My name is Patti and I have lived on the Big Island for over 15 years. (And have enjoyed each year more and more). I live with my best friends
Kai (dog) and Sugar (cat) on the property. I am a very  polite and  responsible person with much Aloha, I love meeting new people from all around the world. I am semi retired,  I own a small company and usually work from home. When I first decided to move to Hawaii from California I came to The Big Island to recuperate from a recent back surgery and stayed with a friend who had recently moved here. Got on the plane after about 12 weeks to go back to my old life. Not a bad one mind you, I didn’t need to run away I choose too!  I was hooked! I sold my home put everything in storage and shipped over my 4Runner! And I have enjoyed each and everyday with no regrets. When you stay here We can talk story or if you wish I will be like a ninja and you will only see me when you check in and/out or if anything is needed.
Looking forward to meeting you.
Mahalo,
Patti

Please keep in mind that the apartment is in Hawaii and you probably will see a few little creatures:)

Natural wonders include Volcanoes National Park, for lava and crater viewing, volcanically heated warm ponds and steam vents (as outdoor saunas) and other wonders of the lush tropics.

Kmec opened in the summer of 2008 for pre-arranged seasonal meditation retreats and private meditation-vacations on request. Additionally, we would like to extend our welcome to Big Island travelers offering cozy cottages and open air kitchen and bath. We offer daily free meditation instructions and practices at our beautiful Balinese meditation pavillion. Additionally, we offer Yoga and nature tours upon guest's request (donations accepted).

name: Amazing Sunset, Amazing Hanauma Bay
host_about:
I am a retired mathematics teacher. I love to host my friends and family. When you choose my airbnb  you become my paying guest, but guest nonetheless. While you are under my roof, I take responsibility for your safety and comfort. I promise to assist you in any which way I can. 

I Have lived in Honolulu for 50+ years.  Love to read, cook, and fiddle around in my yard.

name: Sunrise/ distant ocean view room
neighborhood_overview: It is a safe and quite neighborhood, close to the golf course. The house is situated on a flag lot which offset it from the road but still very conveniently close to Hilo amenities.
host_about:
Aloha!
A little about myself; 
I moved to the Big Island in 1993 from Guam after serving a short stint in the USCG during the Golf War,  then worked as an acute care nurse at our local Hilo hospital for the last 22 years.  

Ive remained mesmerized by this island’s amazing natural beauty, diverse ecosystems, terrains, and love the laid back lifestyle it provides which easily translated into me transforming my house to one I can happily and proudly share with those seeking to explore and experience this amazing island in a relaxed home setting.  

I'm originally  from the Micronesian Island of Yap,  known for its pristine water, manta ray dives ( check out the world-famous  Yap Divers ) and  its colorful and spirited bamboo war dance performed by bare chested natives in lion clothes and grass skirts, something I grew up doing.   
I embrace  cultural diversity and truly enjoy meeting people from all walks of life and all regions in the world.  I take pride in my house and the service that I provide my guests. I value my precious 'free' time by sneaking in sporadic reading here and there  and enjoying the outdoors; camping, hiking, swimming, kayaking, paddle board, and gardening, but most of all, I love traveling and looking forward to seeing a lot more of this amazing world we live in and experience different cultures along the way.

I’m always striving for a balanced lifestyle; healthy living through heath conscious cooking utilizing locally grown, ( a lot are my own home grown) produce, keeping physically active, and inner peace and serenity.   

I look forward to meeting you and I'm excited to host another amazing adventurous soul seeking to experience the Big Island of Hawaii!  

Welcome & E Komo Mai!

Diana

name: B&B, Honeymoon suite, excellent Wi-Fi and desk
neighborhood_overview: This is a quiet neighborhood situated 20 minutes drive outside of Hilo on route to Volcano. I have books and maps available to be used for planning your excursions. The Big Island is a very special place, with one of the few active volcanoes in the world. A must see is the Volcano National Park, where you can drive to the Arch at the ocean,  look in various craters, see volcanic steam vent holes and walk on numerous hiking trails. Here are some free things you can do: the Akatsuka Orchid farm, snorkel and look at the colorful tropical fish small and low key Panaewa zoo, stop at South Point (Ka Lae), the most southern point of US territory, green sand beach, Rainbow falls, the Boiling pots, snorkel/swim with dolphins at Ho'okena or 2 steps, St Benedict`s Painted Church, walk the Hilo down town stores and fruit market place, visit the Captain Cook Monument at Kealakekua bay, walk down the spectacular Waipio or Polulu valleys, travel up Mauna Kea to look at the Observitory and stars throu
host_about:
My wife Lisa and I are a loving and laid back couple. I have been on the island for 20 years and my wife was born and raised here.  We are animal lovers and have a mature dog Milo and an adolescent dog Roman who are allowed inside the common area of the house on the bottom floor. This area includes the living room and kitchen. The Tropical room is also located on this first floor.  We have a menagerie of other animals too! 3 cats who live outdoors...Leo our orange lover boy, Lola our newest playful kitty and Koa who is an energetic crazy but loveable cat and Avery our little bunny rabbit.   

I have created a lush landscaped orchard environment around our 6 bedroom house, by planting almost 200 trees/flowering plants. We enjoy meeting guests who travel from all over the world and learning about them and their culture. 

My wife and I live here full time along with my mother who's more part time.  Cathy is a busy bee and always has a full schedule of events planned for herself around the community.   We enjoy meeting our guests, but we give you your space and also enjoy our space as well.

name: Cozy Cottage Close to Kailua Beach
neighborhood_overview: Our neighborhood is a safe, well lite, family neighborhood. We have a park (Triangle Park) across the street from our property which includes a swing set and jungle gym play area for the kiddos.
host_about:
Aloha, we are husband and wife team, Brandyn and Kristina. We feel so blessed to offer people from all over the world the chance to experience the breath taking scenery and beautiful culture of an island paradise I have called home for my entire life. My family has been in the vacation rental business for over 30 years and it all started with my grandmother Kay (hence Kay's Ali'i Vacation Rental). Now myself, my wife Kristina, and my aunt Lucy have taken over the reins and are continuing the legacy my grandmother started. 

Our families journey in the vacation rental industry started with one small simple unit and slowly evolved into something special for generations to come. We now we have 3 vacation rental properties in Kailua with multiple units on each. Our goal is to offer parties of all sizes the chance to visit our island paradise without having to break their bank accounts. We have 2, 3, & 4 bedroom units for larger groups or extended family getaways. We have 1 bedroom units & large studios for our guests who are traveling with their immediate family and we also have a private rooms for those of our guests who want to get away by themselves or with their significant other to relax and enjoy our beautiful Hawaiian weather. No matter what group size you have we can accommodate you. Take a look at our listing and feel free to message us. We look forward to hearing from you soon. :-)

name: Cozy 1-bedroom in Makiki-Punchbowl
neighborhood_overview: Although it's a very urban neighborhood, it's still friendly and slow-paced. We are on the slopes above Chinatown's shops and restaurants. The location is very convenient, a short drive to Kailua over the Pali, minutes to Manoa, blocks away from the Museum of Art, and close to H1 access in both directions.
host_about:
Just an Argentine living in Hawaii. 
Originally arrived here pursuing a career in Marine Sciences, but somehow became involved in raising a family and things got interesting. 
Until 2014 I was teaching Spanish as a foreign language, and dabbling in literature at the University of Hawaii at Manoa. We relocated to Seattle for a few years, but now we are back.

name: Luana Ola Green Cottage, Ocean View
neighborhood_overview: Luana Ola is on a small dead end road, usually quiet but close to town. You can walk up to town but it is a little hilly.
host_about: Our home is in San Francisco Bay Area. We love Hawaii and bought this property which we hope to retire to in the near future. In the meantime, we will be going back and forth. We are an older couple. We love reading, good  movies and nature.  We have children in California and Seattle and grandchildren. Mohamed has a Ph. D. from UC Berkeley in Energy and Resources.

name: Hibiscus Cottage - Private Puna Rainforest
host_about:
I fell in love with the living energy of the Big Island the first time I was here and I love sharing that energy with visitors.

I worked for Cirque du Soleil as a Stage Manager for over a decade and lived in Japan for two years before moving back to Oahu with my husband and two kids.  I now own and run a coffee shop on Oahu, make jewelry, paint and work for Hawaii Opera Theatre. 

I'm honored to share the aloha spirit with all who choose to welcome it and I aim to provide a quiet, peaceful and relaxing home to stay in during your visit.

name: The Rainforest Room : Lush Nature
neighborhood_overview: Wailea is a quaint old plantation village of about 12 households. It is a very friendly and warm community where we know each other. Every Tuesday, is our Hakalau Market & FoodShare, 3-5 p.m.
host_about:
ALOHA & WELCOME,

Thank you very much for viewing our various accommodations. Our accommodations are located along the lush and tropical Hamakua Coast, 15 miles north of Hilo.
I am  Akiko Masuda, a 3rd generation Japanese woman, born in Honolulu in the 40’s, long before freeways, shopping malls, email, Blackberrys, and cell phones. I have been a writer of children's books, student of tai chi, hula, and zen meditation,  I am a storyteller, hostess, housekeeper, and love caring for our gardens and fruit trees with our weedwhacker and leaf blower. I am the president of the WAILEA VILLAGE HISTORIC PRESERVATION COMMUNITY. I have been living in Wailea Village since' 91, and at that time, was the first person  to buy in this quiet, peaceful country village in 35 years.  Please come and discover the peace and kindness here.

name: Adventure Cottage-Nemaste
neighborhood_overview: a nice place for a walk
host_about:
Steve and Janelle keep a casual Puna lifestyle and run an 6 acre organic farm while you enjoy your visit to the Big Island.
  Janelle is a chef and can cook for any size group. She prefers to feature the crops from the farm and has many years of experience to draw upon. The farm has a booth locally6 on Wednesday nights at a farmers market where eating dinner is the main feature, along with the great music!
   Our home and cottages are a sanctuary and we strive to love all, serve all.  This is an adventure for many and sometimes the beginning of a journey…….

name: " Simplicity combine with comfortability "
neighborhood_overview: The neighborhood around is good, most of the time is very quiet and safe.

name: KV510 Waikiki Beach & dining 2-3 minute walk away!
neighborhood_overview:
Location, Location, Location! We are in the middle of it all.

Much to see and do in Waikiki. The World’s most famous beach is just two short blocks away. Watch the sunsets from nearly any vantage point along the beach and see the Friday night fireworks from the Hilton Hawaiian Village. The nearby neighborhood includes several major hotels and numerous large and small restaurants and nightclubs that cater to every nationality. Ask the kama'aina (locals) for their tips. The Royal Hawaiian Shopping Center and other “World Class Shopping” may be found on Kalakaua Avenue (the street fronting the beach). A few blocks away you will find famous Kapiolani park and the Waikiki Shell, Honolulu Zoo, Waikiki Aquarium, Diamond Head, golfing and many tennis courts.
host_about:
ALOHA and WELCOME!  We are a TEAM of professionals who manage individually owned condo apartments in Waikiki. Our units are well maintained, repaired when necessary and treated for pest prevention. We try not to interrupt our guests, but if the unexpected happens, we do our best to resolve it quickly with the least inconvenience. We look forward to hosting you! 
Aloha & Mahalo, Hawaii Dream Realty LLC RB-19373, 2450 Koa Ave, Honolulu, HI 96815

name: Leilani Rainforest Cottage
neighborhood_overview: Considered  one of the best neighborhoods in East Hawaii
host_about: Aloha , I was born and raised in Santa Cruz, Calif A small surfing town,  I work for a retirement Home as a Food Service Manager , I love the Local vibe in east Hawaii and the laid back culture here come check it out .

name: Walking Distance Kehena Beach Garden Suite Studio
neighborhood_overview: The friendliness of the people, the quiet atmosphere, and the lack of cars driving by is just part of what makes Puna Palisades the most sought after address along the Red Road. The nights are a star gazers dream with no street lights, and the sunrises and sunsets are spectacular.

name: Cozy offgrid cabin in jungle with lava rock shower
neighborhood_overview:
If you're interested in experiencing pristine Hawaii this is a great place to do it. My place offers the convenience of being only five minutes from Keaau, and only a few minutes from a 7-Eleven, the J. Hara Store (with the best fried chicken ever), and fifteen minutes from Hilo, but also out in the country with only one neighbor who isn't even visible or audible. Birds abound, as well as geckos and frogs. Mosquitoes can be a nuisance but use the smoke rings available in the cabin and you'll be good to go.

Lava viewing (when it's flowing) is thirty minutes drive from the house and then a four mile hike or half hour bike ride (if you rent bikes). It's worth it!

The Red Road area of coastal Puna is also half an hour away and is world class and just plain gorgeous. There are many yoga sanctuaries (Hawaiian Sanctuary, etc.) and workshop centers in this area, as well as rich jungle, local exotic fruits and a ton of other cool things going on. The 2018 lava flow hit the
host_about: Lawyer with a thing for building green homes.

name: Rural Luxury for Remote Working and Vacation
neighborhood_overview: We live in a quiet, forested neighborhood.  Parking at the house.  full kitchen and bath.
host_about: We are open for business again.  We have, during the shut down, repainted the apartment and done a deep cleaning.  We have always maintained a very through cleaning standard for our rental,  but we have committed to do a more through sterilizing of the apartment after check out.  We will also not be renting the apartment for 48 hours between guests to give us time to do the increased cleaning protocols.  We have done well in Hawaii to limit the spread of the pre-Covid-19 virus. It our intent to keep both our guests and ourselves safe.  The State of Hawaii has a mandatory  14 day quarantine for incoming visitors until July 31st.   Please (Hidden by Airbnb) the State of Hawaii quarantine requirements before you book.  We would love to host you in our rental. Thank you  David and Bonnie

name: Hawaiian Gem Kings Room
neighborhood_overview:
The big Island has so much to offer.
Sunny with gentle breezes.
Many different activities such as stand up paddle boarding, swimming with dolphins, snorkeling in the crystal blue waters with turtles and multicolored fish, night manta ray viewing.
As well as hikes to the waterfalls, Mauna Kea, and the volcano. There is also whale watching in season.
host_about: We love welcoming new people to Kona.

name: Kona Hidden Oasis
neighborhood_overview: We are in a nice subdivision of all 1 acre lots, kind of a rural setting but pretty close to town and at a cool 1000 ft elevation. The ocean is 3-4 miles away but in view from your lanai. Some beaches are pretty close while other more expansive ones are just up the coast!
host_about: Couple since 1999.  Two children from previous relationship.  Two grandkids. Both retired now and travel quite a lot.

   Our home and cottages are a sanctuary and we strive to love all, serve all.  This is an adventure for many and sometimes the beginning of a journey…….

neighborhood_overview:
Our place is located in the residential area in Hilo.
Your room is facing our yard and next to the yard lives our neighbor.

Also, since it is a residential area surrounded by nature, you might hear dog’s barking, coqui frogs, birds or roosters. We do our best to maintain this B&B as comfortable for you as we can, but there is sometimes things over our control.

name: Orchidland Bed and Breakfast (Private room #1)
host_about: I am a widower.   I like mysteries and historical novels.   I fell in love with Hawaii as a young man of 22 when I was stationed here in the Navy.   It took me 30 years to get back here after I left.   I have been here for the last 18 year.   I know you will love Hawaii as much as I do.

name: Hawaiian Gem Master Suite
neighborhood_overview:
The big Island has so much to offer.
Sunny with gentle breezes.
Many different activities such as stand up paddle boarding, swimming with dolphins, snorkeling in the crystal blue waters with turtles and multicolored fish, night manta ray viewing.
As well as hikes to the waterfalls, Mauna Kea, and the volcano. There is also whale watching in season.
host_about: We love welcoming new people to Kona.

name: B&B, Tropical room, excellent Wi-Fi and desk
neighborhood_overview: This is a pretty quiet neighborhood situated 20 minutes drive outside of Hilo on route to Volcano. I have books and maps available to be used for planning your excursions. The Big Island is a very special place, with one of the few active volcanoes in the world. A must see is the Volcano National Park,  where you can drive to the Arch at the ocean,  look in various craters, walk inside a lava tube, see volcanic steam vent holes and walk on numerous hiking trails. Here are some free things you can do, the Akatsuka Orchid farm, snorkel and look at the colorful tropical fish small and low key Panaewa zoo, stop at South Point (Ka Lae), the most southern point of US territory, green sand beach, Rainbow falls, the Boiling pots, snorkel/swim with dolphins at Ho'okena or 2 steps, St Benedict`s Painted Church, walk the Hilo down town stores and fruit market place, visit the Captain Cook Monument at Kealakekua bay, walk down the spectacular Waipio or Polulu valleys, travel up Mauna Kea to look a
host_about:
My wife Lisa and I are a loving and laid back couple. I have been on the island for 20 years and my wife was born and raised here.  We are animal lovers and have a mature dog Milo and an adolescent dog Roman who are allowed inside the common area of the house on the bottom floor. This area includes the living room and kitchen. The Tropical room is also located on this first floor.  We have a menagerie of other animals too! 3 cats who live outdoors...Leo our orange lover boy, Lola our newest playful kitty and Koa who is an energetic crazy but loveable cat and Avery our little bunny rabbit.   

I have created a lush landscaped orchard environment around our 6 bedroom house, by planting almost 200 trees/flowering plants. We enjoy meeting guests who travel from all over the world and learning about them and their culture. 

My wife and I live here full time along with my mother who's more part time.  Cathy is a busy bee and always has a full schedule of events planned for herself around the community.   We enjoy meeting our guests, but we give you your space and also enjoy our space as well.

name: 1bdr Apt in Honolulu Historical House
neighborhood_overview: The neighborhood is very centrally located.  Very close to downtown business district and Honolulu Harbor.  Oldest neighborhood in Honolulu.  Many historical homes and historical sites nearby.  You will be living at the edge of a rainforest.
host_about: Hi.  I am a retired female business professional from N Calif (San Jose).  I also live and commute frequently to Honolulu (where I was born and raised) throughout the year.  I have traveled extensively for work and pleasure.  I love new experiences and encounters with people.  Cultural nuances always fascinate me and I look for learning something new wherever I go. With much "Aloha" I am happy to open my Honolulu home to all intrepid travelers.

name: Welcome to the Starpod
neighborhood_overview: Kalapana is very special. This land sits at the base of Kilauea caldera which has been creating new earth on a regular basis! Just a few miles down the road is some of the newest land on the planet. At night, guests will hear the crashing of waves as my land is quite close to the coast. Uncle Roberts Wednesday night and Saturday morning market are just a quick bike ride away. Also, the newest black sand beach is just around the corner as well. Kalani Honua, which is only a few miles down the road, offers a wide variety of workshops and classes including dance and yoga. We are also only a 45 minute drive to Volcanoes National Park and 45 minutes to Hilo.
host_about:
I've been living on the Big Island of Hawai'i since 2002 and have developed a beautiful 3.5 acre piece of land at the base of a very active volcano. It's all off-grid with many gardens and fruit trees. I've also established a massage business in Hilo where many of my clients feel like family. I love to travel and to see how people live in other parts of the world. Some of the things I most enjoy doing are being in nature. I've backpacked in the Sierra Nevada mountains as well as the Himalayas. 

My most important goal in life is to live with a sense of compassion and warmheartedness and I equally enjoy hosting people as well as being hosted. I do my best to bring a sense of ease and love whether it's in my own home or someone else's :-)

name: Peaceful Private Hideaway
neighborhood_overview:
Pahoa town is home to the highest concentration of historic buildings in all of Hawaii. The lush landscape is a beautiful contrast to the nearby volcanic settings, and it's got that tropical climate you would expect from the Big Island!

My home sits at the top of Black Sands Beach Community. The smallest neighborhood south of Pahoa with local family homes, eco dwellings and homesteads.

●Volcano National Park- 45-minute drive away. Imiloa Astronomy Center is very cool too!

●Mauna kea Sunset & star gazing- hour and a half away.

● Leilani Estates 2018 lava flow- 15 minutes away.

●Kehena Beach on Red Road, with Sunday drum circle and Dolphins viewing. - in my neighborhood-15 minutes from my house.

● Pohoiki Isaac Hale Beach Park & hot springs- Pahoa/Kalapana- in my neighborhood.

●Kaimu New Beach and Sat morning Market 10 minutes from house

●Kalapana Gardens Lava Flows. 10 minutes from house
host_about:
Hello!
I'm Ginger, a casual friendly host excited to share my home and Hawaii with you.
I am happy to greet you and share local restaurant and adventure ideas...I am also happy to give you space to retreat for a quiet stay.

A Licensed Massage Therapist since 2001, I would be happy to provide a one-hour massage during your stay.

see you soon!

name: Rainbow Retreat with A.C.
neighborhood_overview:
A quiet, country road on a dead-end street, this rural setting has the feeling of the laid-back, relaxed atmosphere which the Big Island has to offer. Only six blocks to the ocean where you can walk along the shore. Also, hiking, biking, fishing, swimming, whale-watching and snorkeling are favorite activities in this locale.
Some of the beautiful drives in the area include the nearby Puna coastline, the Hamakua coast, the drive to the Volcanoes National Park, and the ascent to the top of Mauna Kea.
host_about: I have enjoyed the island life for 30 years in Oahu and now live in my dream destination in the Big Island. Hiking, biking, swimming, yoga, whale watching, and gardening are some of my favorite past times. Also, for the past 25 years I have worked in the spa industry and now I get to share my dream home and my tranquil spa with you and can offer you facial treatments. Originally an L.A. girl, I am now a true local kamaaina woman.

name: Budget 2 blocks to Beach by Aloha-Waikiki 23
neighborhood_overview:
Location, Location, Location! We are in the middle of it all.

Much to see and do in Waikiki. The World’s most famous beach is just two short blocks away. Watch the sunsets from nearly any vantage point along the beach and see the Friday night fireworks from the Hilton Hawaiian Village. The nearby neighborhood includes several major hotels and numerous large and small restaurants and nightclubs that cater to every nationality. Ask the kamaaina (locals) for their tips. The Royal Hawaiian Shopping Center and other “World Class Shopping” may be found on Kalakaua Avenue (the street fronting the beach). A few blocks away you will find famous Kapiolani park and the Waikiki Shell, Honolulu Zoo, Waikiki Aquarium, Diamond Head, golfing and many tennis courts.
host_about: Aloha, I'm Richard and I have been in the travel and tourism industry for over 40 years:)  With ALOHA-WAIKIKI, we offer several vacation rental listings within two blocks of the beach or closer.   Our units range from studios to 1-bedroom apartments sleeping 2-4 guests with garden, city, mountain or ocean views and convenient to shops, restaurants and all forms of transportation on the island.    E Komo Mai (come and belong)!

name: Candlelight Adventure Cottage
neighborhood_overview:
quirky, strong and self sufficient with great natural space. unique and fun.
great place to take a walk.

  Janelle is a chef and can cook for any size group. She prefers to feature the crops from the farm and has many years of experience to draw upon. The farm has a booth locally6 on Wednesday nights at a farmers market where eating dinner is the main feature, along with the great music!
   Our home and cottages are a sanctuary and we strive to love all, serve all.  This is an adventure for many and sometimes the beginning of a journey…….

name: "Angel's Nest 2 @ Kehena Beach"
neighborhood_overview: Our neighborhood is small,quiet, beautiful, peaceful and charming, perfect for strolling thru, either on your way to the beach or just for the sake of a stroll.
host_about: I love being in nature so living in Hawaii is perfect for me.  I like to spend time with my family, especially my grandchildren!

name: Heavenly Hawaii 4 Bed Ocean View⛵️
neighborhood_overview:
Our country side Makaha community has a boat harbor 5 minutes away with access to deep sea fishing and dolphin excursions hiking nearby and great walking areas.
Just one mile down the road is the famous Makaha surf beach if you want to surf or relax on a beautful beach. Pokai Bay is nearby if you like to paddleboard. You can take an enjoyable walk to the golf course with mountain and ocean views and the Makaha valley golf club featuring dining, golf, and more. If you enjoy beaches, golfing, fishing and shopping without the crowds you will love it as much as us! Waikiki is 50 minutes away (depending on traffic) if you do decide to be a “towny” for the day.
host_about: For over a decade, we've shared our homes. As your hosts, we enjoy engaging you with the experiences around your stay, we make sure we are available for questions and concerns and pay attention to detail to make your trip unforgettable. :)

name: Ocean View King with Breakfast
neighborhood_overview: We are easily accessible to all the Big Island attractions such as Volcanoes National Park (1 hour South), Waipio Valley (1 hour North), and the countless sights and adventures along the Hamakua Coast, the Hamakua House is the perfect location to base your Big Island adventure vacation. The legendary Akaka Falls State Park is only 4 miles away from the Hamakua House.  Onomea Bay is only 4 miles away, which is the home of the Hawaii Botanical Gardens. It is an unforgettable drive to get there and the bay is a wonderful place to have a picnic. We are only 1 mile (easily walkable) from the quaint main street of Honomu, HI.  This town was established in the sugar cane plantation era and remains today boasting some wonderful gift shops, two restaurants, a coffee house, and the Island's best Zip Line Tours.
host_about: I'm an outgoing type who values the experience of travel.  Airbnb helps me to afford to travel more.  I love meeting new people.  I grew up in a Bed & Breakfast so hosting comes naturally to me.

name: Yurt Waihuena Farm  MONTHLY bookings only
neighborhood_overview: The North Shore is magic!
host_about: aloha i am mele, i am a treehugger. :)

name: Hale Paradise   A Secure  Private Tropical Getaway
neighborhood_overview: Access private trail to ocean ( 5 minutes), we are in a really beautiful and safe neighborhood. Minutes from the ocean, great for morning and afternoon walks.

name: Windspirit Cottage TA tax #137089228801
neighborhood_overview:
Windspirit Cottage is located in a subdivision where all the parcels are 3 acres. It is countryside. Many people in the area do small farming or are raising animals. One of our neighbors is a horse trainer and can be see working horses in his area on some days. The roads in this are are gravel and some are not well cared for. A low profile car is not recommended. However many people get by ok by driving slowly and picking your route of travel.

There is a Windspirit Cottage in a quiet forest lined with ohia trees.In the season, red lehua flowers bloom beautifully in season.
From the premises, you can see the meadow, horses and donkeys in front of you, and you'll see the blue ocean, white clouds, and sunshine in the distance.It has a very beautiful view where time seems to have stopped for a moment.
A big deep breath while feeling the cozy winds that blow through the place makes the air feel like you are absorbing the stunning sights into your body.
host_about:
We offer vacation rental services to our guests with Aloha and a welcoming spirit. Kayo, my wife, and I are retired and we enjoy visiting with guests from many places.  We have developed a self sufficient lifestyle on 3 acres.  The other residence include 2 cats and a dog and chickens.  We are animal lovers and enjoy talking about them.  My wife and I look forward to helping you enjoy all the beauty of Hawaii.  

LIFE MOTTO:
Living With Heart
Living with Authenticity
Appreciating The Mystery Of Life
Embracing Joy
Cultivating Sacredness In Everyday Life
Expressing Depth and Vision
Building Intimacy And Friendship
Accepting And Learning From Difficulty
Perceiving The World With An Inquisitive, Flexible, Open Mind

name: Cozy and Convenient!
neighborhood_overview: Aina Haina is a safe and convenient residential neighborhood where you can walk to Aina Haina shopping center for all your daily needs.

name: 5 Minute Walk to Magic Sands Beach!
neighborhood_overview:
The home is located off Ali'i Drive on La'Aloa Avenue in a peaceful residential neighborhood known as White Sands Estates. It is a wonderful resting spot for those looking for a quiet retreat after a fun day of play.

This is a wonderful location on the Big Island - warm, dry and nearly always sunny!

It is conveniently located near four popular beaches:

- White Sands / Magic Sands Beach
- 4 mile
- Lyman's Bay to the North
- Kahalu'u beach to the South

Magic Sands Beach features beautiful white sand in the summer, crystalline turquoise water and super fun boogie boarding. 4 Mile is a well-known snorkel and scuba diving spot. World class surfing is 1 mile away at Lyman's Bay to the North and Kahalu'u beach to the South. Kahalu'u also offers easy access to honu (green sea turtles), spectacular snorkeling and beginning surf lessons.

Nearby Keauhou shopping center (2 miles away), has dining, shops, a grocery store, mov
host_about:
I came to Kona for a vacation in 2012 to fulfill the dream of swimming with wild dolphins. The experience was literally life-changing! Within 4 months I let go of my predictable midwestern lifestyle to embrace the adventure of living in Paradise. It was one of the best decisions I've ever made. It feels as if I live in heaven on earth!

Looking forward to sharing the Magic of the Big Island with you!

Aloha and A Hui Hou,

Paul

name: The Elegant Tree Tops Room : The View
neighborhood_overview: Wailea is a quaint old plantation village of about 12 households. It is a very friendly and warm community where we know each other.  Every Tuesday, we have our Hakalau Community Market, 3-5:30 p.m.
host_about:
ALOHA & WELCOME,

Thank you very much for viewing our various accommodations. Our accommodations are located along the lush and tropical Hamakua Coast, 15 miles north of Hilo.
I am  Akiko Masuda, a 3rd generation Japanese woman, born in Honolulu in the 40’s, long before freeways, shopping malls, email, Blackberrys, and cell phones. I have been a writer of children's books, student of tai chi, hula, and zen meditation,  I am a storyteller, hostess, housekeeper, and love caring for our gardens and fruit trees with our weedwhacker and leaf blower. I am the president of the WAILEA VILLAGE HISTORIC PRESERVATION COMMUNITY. I have been living in Wailea Village since' 91, and at that time, was the first person  to buy in this quiet, peaceful country village in 35 years.  Please come and discover the peace and kindness here.

name: The Sunrise Room : First Morning Light
neighborhood_overview: Wailea is a quaint old plantation village of about 12 households. It is a very friendly and warm community where we know each other. Our families know each other. name: 1 Green Sands Oasis Cabin
neighborhood_overview: We have very few neighbors, and it is usually very quiet and peaceful. Green Sands Beach is only 8 miles from our house. You can also visit the southernmost tip of the United States if you drive straight to the point! There are cliffs to jump and sunsets to watch.

name: Mauna Loa Lodge
neighborhood_overview:
Visit the farmer's market Sunday morning at Cooper's Center across the highway and enjoy local foods, crafts, etc. and find great bargains at the the thrift store there.

There are several restaurants in Volcano for a variety of dining options.

name: Honolulu City Lights Studio
neighborhood_overview: It’s a short walk through lush Fort DeRussy Park to the beach, walk along the blue Pacific. The world famous Waikiki Beach beckons you to enjoy its full range of ocean activities or just a quiet sit on its relaxing shore. Shop till you drop along Kalakaua Avenue’s Luxury Row, nearby Royal Hawaiian Center, Waikiki Beachwalk, Ala Moana Center and T Galleria Hawaii by DFS. Fabulous restaurants, cafes, take-out and bars: $ to $$$$: American, Pacific Rim, Hawaiian, Japanese, Chinese and Southeast Asian cuisine.
host_about:
I am a writer living in Waikiki. I've traveled the world but always come home to Hawaii, the most beautiful place on Earth. The surrounding sea sustains and enriches my spirit. An avid jazz lover, I cannot live without the bebop rhythms of artists like Monk, Coltrane, Baker and Bird. Sarah Vaughn is my goddess! Because I write, I also read, mostly novels ... voraciously. Love films, classic or contemporary. The following is one of my favorite odes to life.
Religion says: The body is a sin.
Science says: The body is a machine.
Advertising says: The body is a business.
The Body says: I am a fiesta!
~Eduardo Galeano

name: Another Stay In Paradise! Must See!
neighborhood_overview: Location, Location, Location! We are in the heart of Waikiki. There are so much to do and see in Waikiki. The world’s most famous beach is just one short blocks away (2 minutes walk).
host_about: Aloha and Welcome to the beautiful island of Oahu. We are Chin & Twu, we are co-owners of several condo in Waikiki. We are both professional, friendly and always enjoy helping the tourist what they want to see and do. We have been living here for 15 years now and knows a lot about this island if you have any questions. Mahalo.

name: Puna Rainforest Retreat Hotspring: Purple Passion
neighborhood_overview: There is little reason to leave a 10-mile radius but Hilo is only 24 miles away, Volcanoes National Park 40 miles and the Mauna Kea Observatory, where you can view through telescopes, is 50 miles. Kona is 100 miles over the new saddle road making the connection to the other side in about 2 hours.  Puna Rainforest Retreat is special because you can stay in a private place in a natural setting away from the busy neighborhoods and resorts but are still close enough to enjoy the attractions.
host_about:
I am delighted to share this magical place with all the guests who are drawn here to experience the peaceful beauty and soothing sounds of nature.

This place is a dream come true and I feel blessed everyday to live here.

name: Large Suite in Historic HILO
neighborhood_overview: Downstairs there is a postal shop. As well as Antics Pizza & Ramen. 24hr Laundry mat is just down the street. Bay front is walking distance & full of cute stores as well as cafes, historic shops, restaurants & a few bars. Farmers Market on Wednesdays & Saturdays, plus every Friday there’s a night market with food trucks & live music located by Jackie Rays which is just down the street from our local Tavern that has Open Mic Monday & free karaoke on Wednesday & Thursdays. I’m happy to tell you about my favorite spots if you need any suggestions!
host_about:
My pleasure in life is to see that all people live to their full potentials , be happy and joyful . KEEP SMILING.
ALOHA

name: Wailupe Stream Studio w/Private Access
neighborhood_overview:
This is Upper Aina Haina. A very safe neighborhood with playgrounds and parks. You will see residents of this neighborhood taking walks or jogging at all hours of the day.

There is a shopping center less than a mile away. It has a post office, bank, library, supermarket, restaurants, gym, yoga studio, and Starbucks.

name: Makaha Valley Towers Ocean View
neighborhood_overview: Secluded island paradise, secure, private, quiet. World class white sand Makaha beach one mile away

name: Mauna kea Luxury Getaway Near Volcano
Bright, breezy, peaceful zen room
neighborhood_overview: We live in a beautiful community of about 500 people. Very quiet neighborhood, with close access to a world class black sand beach, children playground, and lots of open spaces to enjoy nature.
host_about: I am a traveler at heart who is highly motivated, active and inspired by people, places and most importantly, nature! I love meeting new people going new places and experiencing new situations! I am a yoga addict, runner,gardener, who knits, draws and travels a lot and believes in travel=education and wisdom! I love anything fermented. I am a big time foodie of anything healthy, organic, and high quality! I love adventures, sailing and having a lot of great laughs! I am very laid back, but like things tidy and organized. Low maintenance kinda person.

name: Charming, Secluded Studio, Centrally Located
neighborhood_overview:
The best restaurants are in Hilo. My favorites are Cafe Pesto, Hilo Bay Cafe, and Reuben's Mexican restaurant. Cronies is another good one for great burgers and sandwiches. Kaleo's in Pahoa is a favorite of locals and visitors.

If you want to cook in and save money instead, I generally grocery shop at Target in Hilo because they have the most items at Mainland prices, but limited selection. Safeway is right next to Target and will have everything you need if you aren't too worried about prices. Foodland in Keaau is the closest to us (8 miles away) and I have a store discount card on your key ring for them. If you prefer health food stores, Kea'au Natural Foods is in the same shopping center as Foodland, right next to Ace Hardware. Island Naturals is in Pahoa and in Hilo.

Hilo also has some good beach parks for snorkeling and taking small kids to, but not much sandy beach areas. The Kona side has all the big, white sand beaches. My favorite beach is Punalu
host_about:
Joel and I realized our dream of moving to Hawaii in 2015 and we have an adult son who lives with us.  

Joel is a tech geek and can help you with any issues you may have.

We tend to keep to ourselves and not hover, but my goal is to make sure you have the most pleasurable stay as possible, so I'm counting on you to let me know if anything needs attention and I appreciate the opportunity to take care of it on the spot.

name: Country retreat to soothe your soul
neighborhood_overview: peaceful rainforest - private, unpaved roads
host_about:
I have an outgoing and friendly personality. I have traveled extensively and  enjoy meeting new people. I moved to Hawaii 3 years ago and to the Big Island 1 year ago. 

I love sharing our beautiful island with the many visitors who arrive here with shear sense of adventure. I enjoy sharing our 'Aloha' spirit with those who choose to visit the Big Island. There is a lot see and do here.

name: Airy apartment at Coconut cottage
neighborhood_overview:
Peaceful, serene. Yet 15 minutes drive to great restaurants in Pahoa and only 25 minutes from Hilo Mall and shopping. Ideally situated for driving to all the islands major attractions.
We are in walking/ cycling distance to the ocean, and there is a beautiful rocky bluff and tidal pools to explore.

The quiet neighbourhood where we live is friendly and quiet. No street lights so you get to see the stars at night, and listen to the coqui frogs chirp. When the surfs up, you can hear the ocean.
host_about:
Hi, 
I look forward to making your stay as easy and as enjoyable as possible. We are keen Nature lovers and explorers and want you to get the most of of your stay
My partner, Malcolm, and I look forward to hosting you and sharing our enthusiasm for the local restaurants, venues and highlights.

name: A  nice experience in Hawaii.
neighborhood_overview: Surround yourself with aloha and natural splendor as you relax and enjoy your stay.
host_about: We love and enjoy hosting .We want our guests to feel at home and have fun staying with us. name: Coconut Cottage/Sunrise Cottages Hawaii
neighborhood_overview: The cottage sits on a half acre directly across the street from the ocean and a wonderful park like setting referred to as 'The Point'.  It's a great place to hang out, relax, enjoy a glass (or bottle) of wine, or a picnic lunch, dinner or just watch the world go by.  The beautiful clothing optional black sand beach is a short 5-10 minute walk.

I have lived on the island half my life and I love adventuring and helping travelers have a good experience while on the island. I’m also an artist, a builder , and coconut climber! Ask me any question about the islands and I will help give the more local advice on where to go and what to do wile visiting. Aloha and mahalo for considering Sunrise Cottages. 

Sunrise cottages is located on the east side of the island, we are not in the tourist trap, we are in the coastal rain forest and a short walk to a beautiful black sand beach.

name: Jo's Hamakua Seaview Getaway
neighborhood_overview:
Our home is located in the once bustling plantation town of Pa'auilo, about 40 minutes north of Hilo, 10 minutes from Honoka'a, 25 minutes south of Waimea, 30 minutes from Waipio Valley, 40 minutes from Waiakoloa and over an hour away from Kona.
It is one of many villages along the Hamakua coast line. Where sugar cane was once harvested and plentiful, diversified agriculture and eucalyptus fields remain. Hamakua reaps the benefits of high rainfall providing for the lush landscape but remarkably has the most temperate climate of any region on the Big Island.
Due to its rich volcanic soil, the Big Island produces some of the highest quality agriculture in the state. Coffee, macadamia nuts, and papaya are just a handful of its world reknowned crops. The Hamakua region itself is home to numerous waterfalls and specialty produce farms like mushrooms and vanilla. Waimea and its rolling hills houses the largest privately owned ranch in the country Parker Ranch; with access t

Ocean view from the road.

Anzu & Bill

neighborhood_overview:
This studio is 20 feet away from the 2 bedroom vacation rental and has 7 acres of grassland surrounding the unit. Peaceful landscape with horses and cows along the drive up, part of the rural beauty of Hamakua coast but close to Hilo.

The stand alone studio has a private patio overlooking the ocean. This is a quiet and peaceful location with a perfect temperature and breeze.

We are located 10 minutes to Hilo, 10 minutes to the nearest beach (Honolii Beach Park), and 50 minutes to the Volcanoes National Park((Re-opened 9/22)
Also Hawaii Botanical gardens and Akaka Falls are nearby. If you have any questions feel free to ask!

Sharon and I built this beautiful, spacious home on 7 acres in 2003 to fulfill a dream of living in Hawaii. Our home takes advantage of an incredible view 5 miles north of Hilo on the Hamakua coast, up slope from the scenic drive and Hawaii Tropical Botanical Garden.  
     Come share our neighborhood with the farms, local horses, space and quiet while you appreciate what we feel is the best of Hawaii.   You will love this area as much as we do.

neighborhood_overview: One block from the city center, established and quiet neighborhood, can walk to ocean front(20 minutes walk). Great for a morning walk.

They are both Japanese traditional medicine practitioners.  No smoking, shoe nor pet in the house.  Leave the house as good as you found it.  Feel at home and enjoy life in Kona

name: Kepuhi Beach Condo with Loft #2144
neighborhood_overview: Kaluakoi Resort, or Kepuhi Beach Resort, was built at the same time as the Sheraton Resort. Our sections of condos were built with full kitchens, the other half as hotel rooms with a restaurant and conference center. The Sheraton has been closed for many years now, but the grounds, pool, parking, etc. are fully maintained and kept up. This gives a very quiet, peaceful complex with endless coves and beaches to explore with very few people. In the condo, there is a binder full of activities, restaurants, and places to visit on Molokai. There is a small convenient store on premises that carries food, snacks, souvenirs, swim suits, etc. The closest large grocery store is 5 miles up the hill in the town of Maunaloa.
host_about:
I live on the Central coast but nothing beats the Island of Molokai for moderate and mild temperatures and warm water. We love snorkeling, scuba diving and swimming and we do all the above on Molokai. We love to charter a fishing boat and listen to Hawaiian music, see some hula and hike.
We hope you like Molokai as much as we do, we have made our vacation home available to you, just as we would like it.
Patrice and Randy

When free I am happy to take to explore. 
I am from Louisiana, and proud of my southern hospitality

name: Oceanfront condo on secluded beach!
neighborhood_overview:
Makaha is the complete opposite of Waikiki, but only an hour away from it. It's a very small town and not over populated like other parts of the island. Well known for some of the best surf on the planet. Lots of great restaurants to eat live entertainment on the weekends. Farmers markets, and hikes in the area. Golf course in view of the condo.

There's a Costco / Safeway, and shopping centers on your way in (25mins away). Disney resort and others are 20mins away with all new shopping center, and classy restaurants. Airport 45mins away. Kailua, Kaneohe, & North shore are both an hour away.


Come get a piece of some old school Hawaii. If you're not into the city life and just want to relax in private, this place is for you!
host_about:
38yr old entreprenuer that lives and born on Oahu Hawaii. Love the ocean and anything to do with the water. Very family oriented.
- Always treat people the way that you want to be treated

host_about: We're 2 dads, originally from Utah & Virginia (with  beautiful daughters, now 18 & 22, must update photo!) who love travel & meeting others & sharing our homes in San Francisco & Hawaii. neighborhood_overview: The beaches & proximity to Haleiwa town. http://www.yelp.com/biz/haleiwa-beach-park-haleiwa,http://www.yelp.com/biz/opal-thai-food-haleiwa, http://northshoreyoga.org/
host_about:
I have traveled to several destinations throughout the world on surfing trips. Australia,Barbados, Costa Rica,France, Indonesia,Mexico, Senegal West Africa and Hawaii. I visited Hawaii and stayed with Malia Macnamara mother of famous surfers Garrethttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Garrett_McNamara & Liamhttp://encyclopediaofsurfing.com/entries/liam-mcnamara. The seed was planted there and the dream was  to create a travel destination with the benefits of exotic places beaches ,food,leisure, yoga,massage,surf,  and safety in one location . I've done it and it's here. I've created LOHAShttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/LOHAS programs for the peaceboathttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peace_Boat. I'm happy to say my most recent travels have taken me to the western U.S. experiencing Burningmanhttp://burningman.org/ & Bhaktifest http://bhaktifest.com/2fest/ it's there where you can see the potential for humanity.   My interests have expanded beyond surfing into  yoga,massage,wellness and slowfood, https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Slow_Foodpermaculturehttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Permaculture,arts,music, etc.... 
 Doing what you love and making a living doing it creates an infectious cycle inspiring people to lead happy productive lives while meeting other interesting inspired people . I think life turns into what we wish & create it to be. What do you think?

name: Quiet Pleasant Room in Kailua
neighborhood_overview: Quiet, lush, green residential neighborhood near main roads to popular sites around Oahu. Nice area to walk around; nearby park, convenience store, YMCA, and ancient Hawaiian heiau (holy site). A few minutes drive to Kailua town, where you'll find great shopping and friendly people. 5-minute drive to world renowned Kailua & Lanikai Beaches as well as Kalama Beach Park. Kailua itself is a great town to browse around; very relaxed and friendly atmosphere with many interesting shops and excellent restaurants.
host_about:
I'm originally from Marin County, CA, and have lived in HI for 37 years. I am retired from teaching English as a Second Language & English at a community college. I enjoy photography; 
I like going for walks, light hikes & sipping a good latte while chatting w/friends. I enjoy nature & art; one & the same in my view. I love to travel, too; it's a feast for the eyes. Hope you feel the same way when you visit Hawaii!

name: Private Deluxe Glamping Hammock Cabana
neighborhood_overview: We are easily accessible to all the Big Island attractions such as Volcanoes National Park (1 hour South), Waipio Valley (1 hour North), and the countless sights and adventures along the Hamakua Coast, the Hamakua House is the perfect location to base your Big Island adventure vacation. The legendary Akaka Falls State Park is only 4 miles away from the Hamakua House.  Onomea Bay is only 4 miles away, which is the home of the Hawaii Botanical Gardens. It is an unforgettable drive to get there and the bay is a wonderful place to have a picnic. We are only 1 mile (easily walkable) from the quaint main street of Honomu, HI.  This town was established in the sugar cane plantation era and remains today boasting some wonderful gift shops, two restaurants, a coffee house, and the Island's best Zip Line Tours.
host_about: I'm an outgoing type who values the experience of travel.  Airbnb helps me to afford to travel more.  I love meeting new people.  I grew up in a Bed & Breakfast so hosting comes naturally to me.

name: Cozy Tropical Retreat
neighborhood_overview:
The home is centrally located to downtown, Ala Moana shopping center, movie theaters, numerous nearby restaurants, 5' away from Kahala Mall and Whole Foods market. Waikiki is just 10 minutes away and 20 minutes to Hanauma Bay for world-class snorkeling. A fantastic home base to see the island and the most gorgeous beaches in the world!
There is also one of the best hikes in Hawaii right by our house.
We are also 2' up the hill from Waialae Ave which has an impressive selection of restaurants and food places. As you walk along Waialae Avenue or explore the back streets of 12th, Kaimuki reveals itself to be a melting pot of great flavors and cuisine from various cultures.
host_about:
We like to spend our free time at the beach surfing. 
We've been to many countries and travel the world quite a few and we always been welcome to wherever we went.
We look forward to meet some awesome people and welcome them to our home and share all the beautiful things that Hawaii have to offer. We want everybody who comes to our home, feel at home and leave Hawaii wanting to come back and have a wonderful impression of the island. We are very excited to share our home to the world.

neighborhood_overview: Papaya Farms Road is a agricultural area with a number of farms and farming communities in the area.
host_about:
Steve and Janelle keep a casual Puna lifestyle and run an 6 acre organic farm while you enjoy your visit to the Big Island.
  Janelle is a chef and can cook for any size group. She prefers to feature the crops from the farm and has many years of experience to draw upon. The farm has a booth locally6 on Wednesday nights at a farmers market where eating dinner is the main feature, along with the great music!

host_about:

We have been honored to be the Super Host since 2015.  We have been doing our best to create a clean, comfortable & hospitable place for our guests.  The culture of Hawaii is "Aloha!" - That means, love, respect & life-giving...  We try to apply all of that into our way of hosting.

Annie & Joy Ohana

name: Hale Mapuana: Best sunrise views/Kahena beach near
neighborhood_overview:
The location of this ohana is close to many local attractions. If you want to get a feel of old Hawaii, this is a good place to stay. Our part of the island has some of the cleanest air you can find in the world! The breezes keep you cool and refreshed most of the time.
We live off of the famous RED ROAD, which is a scenic drive to see the 2018 lava flow into the ocean one way, then up to historic Pahoa town, where there are many quaint dining experiences. There are also farmers markets, concerts, and shops. If you drive north, you have access to beautiful ocean and jungle views all along the way..
There is even KAHENA (a small black sands beach nearby), where you can sometimes see dolphins, and if you are a good swimmer this is a place to snorkel and swim. You do need to know, though, that this is a clothing optional beach.

name: Iconic Views - Waikiki DiamondHead
neighborhood_overview: You will be staying up Maunalani Heights. Our location is one mile up the slopes of Maunalani, which resides above the quaint town of Kaimuki , full of fabulous eateries and specialty shops. A few minutes away is the well known Farmers Market at Kapiolani Community College which is a must do Saturday mornings, and as you can see by the view, hiking up Diamond Head and taking in the breathtaking views atop the dormant volcano is amazing! Also in the area is the local Diamond Head Theatre and our famous Waikiki beaches.
host_about: Aloha! We are an airline family and have the good fortune of travel! We enjoy visiting new places, experiencing new foods and engaging and experiencing new cultures. We look forward to sharing our aloha while you enjoy your Hawaiian experience.

name: Hibiscus room
neighborhood_overview: Our neighborhood is an old Hawaiian village. Most of our neighbors live in the the home they and their parents were raised in. The spirit of aloha is alive and well. We all watch out for each other. We are all off the grid. Being 2.5 miles from the ocean and 7 miles to town are part of what makes this a sweet and special spot.

name: 1 Room in Luxury Home, Amazing Ocean View Sunsets
neighborhood_overview:
The Kealakekua Bay area has always been our top pick of places on the Big Island. It's green, lush and beautiful and you can still feel the old Hawaiian feeling and culture. It's a great location for snorkeling, adventure, scuba diving and to swim with wild dolphins.
The airport is 6 miles north of Kailua-Kona. Our house is perfectly located 14 miles south of Kailua-Kona. Kona Paradise is another 12 miles south of our house. Our house is close to everything you can possible need. Just 5 minutes away from a large grocery store. One of the biggest hospitals on the Island is close as well. Several ATM and banks are 8 minutes away. Kealakekua Bay, Ke'ei Beach and Honaunau, also called Two Step, are just a few miles away and offers great snorkeling at beautiful coral reefs, the possibility to watch wild dolphins and large turtles. You can kayak over to the Historical Captain Cook monument and snorkel at one of Hawaii's best coral reefs. The Coffee Shack is just a few minutes away. The
host_about: I am person who loves to travel.

name: Lucky Studio Honolulu-Ala Moana/Wi-Fi\/ 30 day +
neighborhood_overview:
Super convenient Makiki location, three blocks from Blaisdell Center (shows/ concerts); Safeway supermarket and Longs drugs about 2/3 blocks away, Honolulu Museum of Art 1 block away, WholeFoods Market 5 minutes away, drive to Waikiki less than 10 minutes, Ala Moana Shopping Center also about 5-7 minutes away, easy access to H1 (less than one block away).
Lots of restaurants and fast food locations all around the vicinity, walking distance: “Chick Fil A”, Mc Donald’s, Dew drop Inn” is one of my favorites Chinese restaurants in the island. “Auntie Pastos” also close by if you’re craving Italian fare. Many Japanese and sushi locations nearby, as well as Vietnamese and Thai.
host_about:
Aloha! I'm a social worker and crystal healing teacher living in Honolulu with my daughter and our dog Papi. I enjoy the laid back outdoors lifestyle here in Hawaii. I'm originally from Brazil and have been in Hawaii since 1996. 
My passion is healing, spirituality and crystals.  
I really enjoy sharing my love of healing with people, it is a fun and enriching experience.

"The Journey is the Destination"

neighborhood_overview: Located on the wide open end of Waikiki - steps to the beach, park and zoo.  A short walk to the public library, Waikiki Shell, Farmers markets and a large grocery store (20 minutes).
host_about: I have lived in Hawaii for over 30 years after moving here for work.  I enjoy the sun, sand, people, and color.  I enjoy classical music, exercise.

name: Spacious Waikiki Studio on 20th floor!
neighborhood_overview: Just outside the building, you'll find shopping, restaurants, and nightlife. Best of all, the world famous Waikiki Beach is just a few minutes walk away. Everything is within walking distance, but if you choose to venture out farther, there are major bus and trolley lines half a block away from the property. If shopping is your thrill, shop at the world-renowned Ala Moana Shopping Center, Hawaii's largest mall, less than two miles away! The Hawaii Convention Center is less than a mile away, and Hawaii's historical sites like Iolani Palace, Chinatown, and Downtown Honolulu are less than 4 miles away.
host_about: I am the property manager for this unit

name: Tropical Canopy Guest Studio in Hawaii
neighborhood_overview: Ten minute walk to the black sand beach of Kehena, where there may be dolphins to play with. A short drive will land you at Unlce Roberts Kava bar, where you will often find the Uncles playing old Hawaiian country songs on Wednesday night. Also, at Uncle Roberts is the Saturday morning farmers market.
host_about:
Aloha, I made a lifestyle decision to move to Hawaii in 2005. I fell in love with the Big Island for the first time in 97. Since then I've explored homesteading and a closer connection to our land. I have been building and creating. Now I am ready to share the house with travelers who visit this magical place. I am into a peaceful sustainable existence, that gives rest to a fast moving civilization. Sometimes it is enough to just look at the stars, and here you can see them well, or just return to the original TV, a nice relaxing fire. And I love to cook on the flames, so simple, so good. Sharing food is my favorite form of communion. I love slow cooking, whether it be smoking or stew making. Slower and longer is just better if you ask me. 

I am a builder, and as a builder the most gratifying thing is to see people enjoying the manifestations that have been created. Sometimes the focus of what it means to construct something for the utilitarian purpose gets lost in the process. But, the magic is always underlying everything, so many times pure serendipity is right there, reminding us. The intention is everything and construed in all the stones carried, wood carved, land sculpted and much, much else. When the energy is pure, then it is easily conveyed or felt. This land is unfolding as the volcano has taught us. All who become part of this history will see how powerful is the asking. My experience here is that there is an instant reflection in the asking. Have fun and come and see...After all this is some of the newest land on this planet.

name: Hamakua Bedroom on Main Strip of Honokaa Town!
neighborhood_overview: This listing is on the Main strip of Historic Honokaa town, you can walk to all the shops, restaurants and pub! It's only 10 mins from Waipio Valley where there's waterfalls and black sand beach! Plus we are central which makes it easy to go to Kona or Hilo and back! Also makes it easy to go to Mauna kea and the white sand beaches on the east side!
host_about: I'm an entrepreneur, and best selling author. In my spare time I often mentor and do inspirational speeches for young entrepreneurs, to inspire them to follow their dreams. I love to tahitian dance, surf, spearfish, hike, and martial arts!

name: Affordable Ocean View in Paradise
host_about:
We live in a little town called Helen, Georgia. Helen is a unique Bavarian-style tourist town, where we are lucky enough to run tourist activities year round. My wife and I are ordained ministers and we have a business called On the River Weddings and we help couples make their dreams come true with lovely events in our classic little chapel on the banks of the Chattahoochie River.
When we first bought our little condo in Hawaii, it was simply a place to get away for a little R and R in the winters. We came to love the little town of Makaha, Oahu, and when we learned about Airbnb, we realized it would be a great way to share our feelings about the place and help people realize their dreams of coming to Hawaii for a vacation or a honeymoon in an affordable way. There is little to no traffic, very few homes on the coast, canopied trees over the road opening into crashing waves on the black lava! Breathtaking!! Our sweet town of Pahoa is 7 miles away with incredible restaurants, markets, health food store, bank, post office, library etc. The beautiful town of Hilo is 27 miles away with wonderful history and an incredible waterfront.

We enjoy the quiet laid back vibe we have on this side of the island and one of the cleanest airs on the planet!   Our favorite part of this property is all the fruit trees and the plush landscape !

Of all the subdivisions in lower Puna, HPP is closest to Hilo, meaning shorter commute times to Hawaii’s second largest city – the business heart of east Hawaii.

name: Sweet Upstairs Corner Ocean View Studio on Molokai
neighborhood_overview: Kepuhi Beach Resort, also known over time as Kaluakoi Villas, or West Molokai Resort, lies on the west end of Molokai, and were built originally  as part of the Sheraton Kaluakoi Villas Resort and Golf Course, which is now closed and seems to be returning to nature!   The West coast of Molokai has wide open savannah spaces, trails for hiking and biking, and wonderful, wild, private beaches, with long stretches of sand and surf, and hardly any company!  Nearby Papohaku beach is 3 miles long of lovely sand, and it is likely you will be alone.  Not all beaches are ideal for swimming at all times, but there are several nearby that are generally protected and accessible.  Forested high altitude cloud forest, nature preserves, sea cliffs, historical points of interest.  Mountain biking, surfing, fishing, snorking, whale watching, rodeo, the mule ride down the cliffs to the Kalaupapa peninsula, and the Molokai Hoe canoe race to Honolulu.  Saturday Farmers Market in Kuanakakai.  Organic produc
host_about: I live in Seattle with Albert, raising 5 kids who are launching now, and our Molokai condo has become our 2nd home!  They say Molokai chooses you, and she sure did.  We like travel, hiking, yoga, snowshoeing, good food, good reading, and just hope to be doing a lot more of all this!

There are so many breath taking places to explore in the lower Puna side. Walk around Pahoa Village, do a little shopping, munch on fish and chips, or enjoy a shot of noni juice. Get your beach gear, picnic basket ready and head down to the new black sand beach at Isaac Hale beach park and e
