name: Harmonic Celestial Temple #2
neighborhood_overview: I have lived in this neighborhood for 18 years and all my neighbors are great, no one bothers you at all, they are very conscious and respectful of your space and that you are here for vacation.
host_about:
Aloha. I am Celeste and I invite you to my beautiful sacred home here in Captain Cook on the Big Island of Hawaii. My passion is taking people out to swim with the dolphins, which I have facilitated for 22 years as well as facilitating swims with the South Pacific Humpback Whales in Tonga. I love animals and do whatever I can to save them. Being in Nature is important to me and here on the Big Island we are surrounded, it is Paradise. 
My home is inviting and welcoming to those who would like to come and relax and feel the healing energies that my environment offers you. I look forward to meeting you and having you stay. If you would like dolphin swims I am available to bring you to these amazing animals, it is something you will never forget! Blessings to you~~~~Celeste

name: Oceanview Room
neighborhood_overview: Very safe area, elevation which makes it nice and cool, quite, nice neighbors, conveniently close to all Hilo town has to offer.
host_about:
Aloha!
A little about myself; 
I moved to the Big Island in 1993 from Guam after serving a short stint in the USCG during the Golf War,  then worked as an acute care nurse at our local Hilo hospital for the last 22 years.  

Ive remained mesmerized by this island’s amazing natural beauty, diverse ecosystems, terrains, and love the laid back lifestyle it provides which easily translated into me transforming my house to one I can happily and proudly share with those seeking to explore and experience this amazing island in a relaxed home setting.  

I'm originally  from the Micronesian Island of Yap,  known for its pristine water, manta ray dives ( check out the world-famous  Yap Divers ) and  its colorful and spirited bamboo war dance performed by bare chested natives in lion clothes and grass skirts, something I grew up doing.   
I embrace  cultural diversity and truly enjoy meeting people from all walks of life and all regions in the world.  I take pride in my house and the service that I provide my guests. I value my precious 'free' time by sneaking in sporadic reading here and there  and enjoying the outdoors; camping, hiking, swimming, kayaking, paddle board, and gardening, but most of all, I love traveling and looking forward to seeing a lot more of this amazing world we live in and experience different cultures along the way.

I’m always striving for a balanced lifestyle; healthy living through heath conscious cooking utilizing locally grown, ( a lot are my own home grown) produce, keeping physically active, and inner peace and serenity.   

I look forward to meeting you and I'm excited to host another amazing adventurous soul seeking to experience the Big Island of Hawaii!  

Welcome & E Komo Mai!

Diana

name: Adventure Treehouse - As featured on HGTV!

From the house only one house is visible in the back distance but you can occasionally hear our front neighbors. There are abandoned vehicles down the road but that's not uncommon in rural neighborhoods on the Big Island.
host_about:
Aloha! 
I was raised in Bountiful, Utah. After I finished my degree in psychology I moved to Oahu to teach at a private boarding school. I taught for a total of 5 years and then decided to build a tiny off-grid house! I currently work for the University of Hawai'i Manoa & where I am getting my Master's of Social Work degree. In my spare time I paint, surf, hang out with friends or family, read, hike, and play with any furry critters that may come my way.

name: Family Outdoor Hammock Camping Cabana
neighborhood_overview: We are easily accessible to all the Big Island attractions such as Volcanoes National Park (1 hour South), Waipio Valley (1 hour North), and the countless sights and adventures along the Hamakua Coast, the Hamakua House is the perfect location to base your Big Island adventure vacation. The legendary Akaka Falls State Park is only 4 miles away from the Hamakua House. Onomea Bay is only 4 miles away, which is the home of the Hawaii Botanical Gardens. It is an unforgettable drive to get there and the bay is a wonderful place to have a picnic. We are only 1 mile (easily walkable) from the quaint main street of Honomu, HI. This town was established in the sugar cane plantation era and remains today boasting some wonderful gift shops, two restaurants, a coffee house, and the Island's best Zip Line Tours.

Our listing is clean, comfortable, full of hotel- style amenities, and the true definition of Aloha Spirit. We look forward to meeting and introducing you to our little piece of Aloha. Come & Stay with us Cheers, MnB

name: Home of ALOHA, 1bdrm, HI Kai, w/ukulele lesson!
neighborhood_overview: Our neighborhood is very safe and located just minutes away from beautiful beaches, including Hanauma Bay.  We are also very close to Koko Marina, where one can find many places to eat, shop, bank and even visit the movie theatre!  We recommend Bubbies Homemade Ice Cream and Desserts and also Kokonuts Shave Ice & Snacks for first time visitors! There are great places to hike that are within walking distance!
host_about: I am from the Island of O’ahu, born and raised! My husband and I have been married for 33 years and have 4 grown daughters, ranging in age from 20 - 32 . . . We also have a 7 yr old granddaughter.  I love to bake, cook, hike and read.  We both love to travel and sit in little cafe’s, sipping on lattes!

name: Secluded Tropical Bungalow on Sacred healing land
neighborhood_overview: There are local art and music events happening throughout the week.  Ecstatic dances on Sundays and Thursdays are continuing in Hilo.  Open Mic every Monday at the Kava Bar, and Uncle Robert's every Wednesday at Kalapana are still lively events .  Makuu Farmers Market is loaded with local produce, crafts and more every Sunday.  Kehena Beach, Shipman's Beach, Mermaid Tide pools and a new Bland sand beach created by the lava are a few local secret spots open to visit. This is authentic Hawaii, an area where time can stand still. There is little to no traffic, very few homes on the coast, canopied trees over the road opening into crashing waves on the black lava! Breathtaking!! Our sweet town of Pahoa is 7 miles away with incredible restaurants, markets, health food store, bank, post office, library etc. The beautiful town of Hilo is 27 miles away with wonderful history and an incredible waterfront.
host_about: Gray and I are so grateful to be stewards of this magical land! We love to do our best to create a wonderful experience for our guests.  Looking forward to meeting you and sharing the beauty, peace and calm of this land with you.  We love to start our day with a quiet walk in the jungle and our way back gather produce from our neighborhood fruit stands.  We enjoy the quiet laid back vibe we have on this side of the island and one of the cleanest airs on the planet!   Our favorite part of this property is all the fruit trees and the plush landscape !

name: Lava Lookout: Pele  / full equipped kitchen /
neighborhood_overview:
Kalapana is unique. Come visit the magic of a 30 year old lava flow with active lava flowing less than 12 miles away. Even when the lava isn't flowing, this is definitely one of the most unique places on earth. Pahoa, a super awesome little village is 20 minutes away - or run to Uncle Roberts for the stop and shop or nightly night market on Wednesdays (not to be explained - just to be experienced :)).

There is a lovely (clothing optional) black sands beach (Kehena) very nearby, where you can often see spinner dolphins and sea turtles in the distance. Although the region is in flux, Puna remains very beautiful.
host_about:
As a host on some of the newest earth that exists; I’m passionate about the natural world (worked in solar & LEDs), love animals (fostered 100's of kittens & worked at a farm sanctuary), and am into social justice - helped build a straw bale on an Native American reservation years ago.

I've seen much of the US (all 50 & PR) but am looking to explore much more of the world while making a positive impact on the environment, people and animals.

name: Mango Suite-private studio close to best beaches
neighborhood_overview:
Situated on Oahu's west coast, Makaha offers seclusion from the bustling city life of Honolulu, while still being within a comfortable distance for a day trip. Renowned for its beautiful beaches and incredible surf, Makaha has an inviting, laid-back atmosphere that appeals to both residents and visitors alike. Its most famous landmark, Makaha Beach Park, is a popular spot for surfing, diving, and simply enjoying the sun. Makaha's appeal lies in its relative seclusion, community feel, and access to stunning natural landscapes. From the verdant Makaha Valley to the pristine beaches, residents are never far from an outdoor adventure. Makaha offers the best of both worlds: quiet, country living, and access to major retail/shopping centers 20 minutes away!

Our newly built home sits on a large, 2-acre lot with tropical fruit trees and flowers. Just 1/4 mile from beautiful Papaoneone Beach, 1 mile from world-famous Makaha Beach, and within 4 miles of the best beaches in Hawaii - M
host_about: Aloha! We are Robin and Aki. Thanks for your interest in our private guest suite and we look forward to meeting you! We live, work, and play in beautiful Makaha, Oahu. We can usually be found in the water surfing/diving, exploring waterfalls, or in a yoga class. Aki owns a handmade sea jewelry business while Robin works full-time as a public school teacher in Waianae. Summer keeps us busy picking mangoes on our small farm, Aloha Fruits.

name: Pua's Patch: The Tivaevae Room
neighborhood_overview:
I live within walking distance of the finest botanical garden on the island and perhaps in the state. It truly is the "Onomea Scenic Route" and I recommend you walk it, drive it, get to know it.

My home is also literally a 5 minute drive to Hilo's finest surf spot. . . the famous Honoli'i!

We have waterfalls, beaches, jungle hikes, active volcanos!

What we DON'T have are a lot of restaurants or services open on Sunday evening. And our internet connections can be sketchy sometimes.

When you visit Hilo, check out where we are on a GLOBE, and then please remember where we are on the planet!!
host_about:
We are retired, active, travelers--kamaʻāina to Hilo and Oʻahu. We love the outdoors and the ocean, and are passionate about competitive outrigger paddling.

Please check out the links to our other listings: The Blue Room, The Tivaevae Room, and/or The Plantation Inn (rented separately or as an entire house)

name: Lava Lookout: Kāne - off grid suite
neighborhood_overview: This is a unique place and attracts many different people, as well as tourists. We only ask that you act and treat others as you would like to be treated. Be respectful of the space and the culture that is lava life. Please understand that while active flow may not always happen, volcano and ocean views always are.
host_about:
As a host on some of the newest earth that exists; I’m passionate about the natural world (worked in solar & LEDs), love animals (fostered 100's of kittens & worked at a farm sanctuary), and am into social justice - helped build a straw bale on an Native American reservation years ago.

I've seen much of the US (all 50 & PR) but am looking to explore much more of the world while making a positive impact on the environment, people and animals.

name: West Hawaii Room (tax included)
neighborhood_overview: We live in a residential neighborhood where it is peaceful and quiet, far above the traffic noise of Ali'i Drive and the Mamalahoa Hwy.  The closest market is a corner store just under 2 miles away.  It is a steep walk down and back.  We recommend you rent a car or plan on using Uber throughout your stay.  Once you are in town, you can rent bicycles, scooters (no motorcycle license required) or catch the Kona Trolley which travels from the Kona Commons Shopping Center to the Sheraton Keauhou each day.  This open-air trolley stops at the markets, beaches, and shops all along Ali'i drive and is a relaxing way to get around town.
host_about:
I'm a Silicon Valley professional having the time of my life building my startup.  My daughter, Aurora, manages our location in Santa Clara. She works nearly full time and is attending college.  My husband, Bill and I, love playing golf, snorkeling in Hawaii and going for a drive on the coast with the top down on our Mustang.
I've lived in Silicon Valley nearly all my life and I enjoy making our place home to guests whether they are with us for a day or for multiple years.
I have a commitment to people and am out to have everyone recognize and express their brilliance in the world for the well being of humanity and our world.

name: Spacious apartment in HILO
neighborhood_overview: Being so close to down town Hilo you will definitely have the chance to experience all Bay front has to offer. From cute stores to cafes. Historic shops to restaurants & local bars, all within walking distance. We have a Farmers Market on Wednesdays & Saturdays with fairly priced produce & so much more. Plus every Friday there’s a night market with food trucks & live music located by Jackie Rays which is just down the street from our local Tavern that weekly has Open Mic Monday & free karaoke on Wednesday & Thursdays. I’m happy to tell you all about my favorite spots if you might need any suggestions!
host_about:
My pleasure in life is to see that all people live to their full potentials , be happy and joyful . KEEP SMILING.
ALOHA

name: Molokai Dreams Ocean View Studio Condo
neighborhood_overview: Our condo is set among other buildings in the resort with pathways to walk and only steps away from the beach.
host_about: We love our special spot in paradise and hope you will enjoy the beauty, peace and tranquility of the island of Molokai and the wonderful people who live there.

name: Seaview Pink House
host_about:
Hi, I'm Fawni... 
I've been living in the Hawaiian islands since 2011 (Maui and Hawaii) and it's my soul's Home! It's a true joy for me to share it with others. I'm a spiritual counselor that helps people transform their lives through self-awareness and growth. I also love just being in nature and growing food in my garden. It's my mission to share the magic life has to offer with those who are ready to see it.

name: Paradise on a Budget #4
neighborhood_overview:
Located just outside of world famous Waikiki on the island of Oahu in the City of Honolulu Hawaii. Perfect location for the explorer who is ready to discover all that this island has to offer. Located on bus line #3 & #9 (#9 is direct connect to airport) getting around without a car is simple & convenient. If a car works better for you, I have PARKING (subject to availability)!!!
My neighborhood is typical eclectic Urban Honolulu. My home was built in 2004 & is modern & comfortable.
host_about:
Aloha!!  I am a friendly, happy & thankful gay man!!  I moved to Hawaii over 15 years ago from Los Angeles in search of true happiness.  I found it!!!  I love my life!!!
Please allow me to share my modern urban oasis with you & help to make your Hawaiian experience a memorable one!!!

name: tiny home 1 - private stay w/ kitchen near VNP
neighborhood_overview: It's quite and peaceful. In 3 acres lot Houses  which bring the place unique in its own private place in the jungle.

name: King Studio with Daybed (sleeps 4)
neighborhood_overview: Just outside the building, you'll find shopping, restaurants, and nightlife. Best of all, the world famous Waikiki Beach is just a few minutes walk away. Everything is within walking distance, but if you choose to venture out farther, there are major bus and trolley lines half a block away from the property. If shopping is your thrill, shop at the world-renowned Ala Moana Shopping Center, Hawaii's largest mall, less than two miles away! The Hawaii Convention Center is less than a mile away, and Hawaii's historical sites like Iolani Palace, Chinatown, and Downtown Honolulu are less than 4 miles away.
host_about: I am the property manager for this unit

name: Luxury Farmhouse Upper Suite
Waikiki Canal view Studio WiFi Gym Pool A/C Beach
neighborhood_overview: 5 min walk to 7/11 . 15 mins walk to New International Market. 15 mins walk to Famous Waikiki Beach. 10-10 mins walk to DFS and Royal Hawaiian Shopping Center. 25 mins ( walking distance ) to Honolulu Zoo.

name: 3 Green Sands Oasis Cabin 3
neighborhood_overview: We have very few neighbors, and it is usually very quiet and peaceful. Green Sands Beach is only 8 miles from our house. You can also visit the southernmost tip of the United States if you drive straight to the point! There are cliffs to jump and sunsets to watch.

name: Kalanikai Paradise  STVR Permit # 19-376086
neighborhood_overview: Kalanikai is located in Kailua Village, right in town.
host_about: Bruce and Bernice are married and love Kailua and the Big Island of Hawaii. We bought our second home in 2003. We rented it as a long term rental for several years. At this time in our lives we are spending time at our place and sharing it with other's is a way to 'have our cake and eat it too'. We hope you will love Hawaii as much as we do and make wonderful memories at Kalanikai and on the Big Island.

name: Pua Blossoms' Escape
neighborhood_overview: Beautiful grounds and friendly folks from all over the world.  The subdivision is  located off La'aloa  street which connects to the main Highway and Alii Drive ..
host_about: I am very mellow with simple needs.  I have two dogs, Minnie & Bonez and a very loud Indian Ringneck Parakeet named Hoku.  Hoku is loud in the morning  and wakes up between 6:45 - 7am.  I suggest bringing noise canceling headphones, especially if you sleep in.  I try to keep my home clean because I do most of the cleaning.  If you’re a MAGA/Trump supporter, you are not welcome in my home!  Mahalos!

name: Bebo's Basecamp near Waipio, Hapuna, Hilo, Kona
neighborhood_overview:
We are also located in an area with the best cycling on the island. Perfect location if you are a cyclist. As we are located in the hills above honokaa, a vehicle is a must. We are 5 min drive to Honokaa town and 20 min drive to Waimea. We are very centrally located half way between Kona and Hilo. We are only 40 min from Mauna Kea visitor center, a must see when visiting the Big Island. We have plenty of local recommendations to share with our guests.

There are no street lights in the area, so it is very dark at night. It may be a challenge to find us at night for the first time.
host_about:
We are friendly, warmhearted, easy going, semi retired, former kona coffee farmers.
We welcome warmhearted, friendly and low maintenance guests that have adventurous spirits and the will to explore. 
Our purpose and passion is taking care of the land and Ohana "family" that gives us so much.
We love to talk story in the evening or over a morning cup of coffee or hearing guests talk about their adventures.
We are happy to give good local recs on places to see, things to do, as well as places to eat.
We love promoting our award winning Kona Coffee on a personal level and  getting to know our guests and customers for who they really are rather than just what it is they do for a living.
By being ourselves. guests often thank us for making them feel so welcome and part of our Ohana.
We love meeting guests from around the world and continue to grow our Ohana globally as well as locally.
We love Airbnb and look forward to bringing you fond lifelong memories of your Hawaiian adventure.
See you soon
Aloha.....................Bebo and Karen

name: Pua's Patch: The Blue Room
neighborhood_overview:
We live within walking distance of the finest botanical garden on the island and perhaps in the state. It truly is the "Onomea Scenic Route" and we recommend you walk it, drive it, get to know it.

Our home is also literally a 5 minute drive to Hilo's finest surf spot. . . the famous Honoli'i!

We have waterfalls, beaches, jungle hikes, active volcanos!

What we DON'T have are a lot of restaurants or services open on Sundays.

When you visit Hilo, check out where we are on a GLOBE, and then please remember where we are on the planet--the most isolated inhabited land on earth. People who have chosen to live on a rural, sparsely inhabited, outer island in the middle of the Pacific.

Do not expect to find things (or resources) as they are in _________.
host_about:
We are retired, active, travelers--kamaʻāina to Hilo and Oʻahu. We love the outdoors and the ocean, and are passionate about competitive outrigger paddling.

Please check out the links to our other listings: The Blue Room, The Tivaevae Room, and/or The Plantation Inn (rented separately or as an entire house)

name: Idyllic Stay at the Treetop Retreat
neighborhood_overview: We are about 3 miles away from the last volcanic activity and it’s an exciting time on the Big Island. The area is several hundred acres of small farms that produce fruit and other things. Puna (the district) offers a unique glimpse at Hawaii away from the high rises and contrived Hula shows of Waikiki and the mega-resorts. Guest come to Puna to relax and get away from it all, and to see lava flows and waterfalls!
host_about: Easygoing, well-travelled European that traded the old world for an island in the Pacific some 20 years ago. Enjoys coffee, conversations, a good book and interesting experiences.

name: Living On Aloha! In Oceanview, Hawaii
neighborhood_overview: Oceanview is the largest subdivision in the United States. The roads are private and sometimes they refer to the upper regions as "The wild west!" it is a unique, raw and beautiful place to drive around but I don't recommend visiting the neighbors without an invitation. The Oceanview market is located around the corner and 2 miles down hill on Lehua St. There are coffee and pizza shops, grocery store and gas. Saturday mornings there is a large swap meet across the highway next to Malama Market, our other grocery store. L&L grill serves local favorites at a reasonable price. There are also a few restaurants around. Thai and Family dining.
host_about:
E Komi mai! Welcome, I am a woman raising a wonderful teenager who was lucky enough to find her dream home in Hawaii where I have lived for 40 years. I am a teacher and used to be an active member of our local community theater in Kona and Hilo. I have lived in Oceanview for just over five years and love it. I never want to live without coffee, chocolate or macnuts and Kau has it all, as well as some exquisite scenery and wonderful people. 
I have traveled all over the world and done some Airbnb in California and Oregon. I love to meet new people, learn about their dreams and travel experiences. I’m always open to hearing about your tips and any hidden Jems  you find here on the Big Island. 
Aloha 
Catherine

name: Sweet 1br home away from home
4 Green Sands Oasis Cabin #4
neighborhood_overview: We have very few neighbors, and it is usually very quiet and peaceful. Green Sands Beach is only 8 miles from our house. You can also visit the southernmost tip of the United States if you drive straight to the point! There are cliffs to jump and epic sunsets to watch.

name: AirBnB nr Pearl Harbr, a Relaxing Space 31 day min
neighborhood_overview:
This apartment is centrally located on Oahu, making it the perfect place to consciously explore the entire island. Usually, without traffic, the space is 10 minutes from the Honolulu Airport, 15 minutes to downtown Honolulu, 25 minutes to Waikiki, 20 minutes to Kailua and 45 minutes to the North Shore.
Relax or work from this airy space, while maintaining a close relationship with the `āina (land).

You'll also be close to nearby historic and local sites:
*Pearl Harbor Arizona Memorial
*'Aiea He'iau Loop Trail Hike (a Hawaiian medicinal hei'au with a beginner-friendly hike and incredible views)
*Aloha Stadium Swap Meet (Hawaii's premiere outdoor market, on Saturday, Sunday, and Wednesday)
*Pearlridge Mall with a Saturday Farmer's Market
*Aiea Park with a local Friday Morning Farmer's Market, basketball and running tracks

***Only non-smoking guests who have been vaccinated (including booster) may stay with us.
host_about: SUP surfer, physical comedian, dancer, actor, writer, yogi, dog--cat loving snowboarder who has appeared on Broadway. Home-grown in Hawai'i, and spent many years in NYC. I have an MFA in Writing and Acting from the New School in NYC, have taught at NYU. I do Yamuna body work to align the skeletal system, love eating organic fruits and vegetables and being in the ocean at dawn. Respect for the `aina (land) and local people is needed to stay here.

name: Aloha Suite Near the Sea I, 3 Block Walk to Beach!
neighborhood_overview:
THE LOCATION

This studio's excellent location situates you just a short walk to famous Waikiki Beach, where you can surf, snorkel and wade in the glittering Pacific Ocean. While walking along the warm sandy beaches, you may see breaching Humpback whales or green sea turtles, depending on the season!

Along the main strip of Kalakaua Avenue, you'll find shopping, dining, resort activities and more! Take home some of the beauty of Hawaii with handmade art pieces and jewelry found right along the strip.

Just 1 minute away is Hy's Steak House offering an extensive wine list, superb steaks, and seafood. For a themed barefoot bar right on the beach, visit Duke's for breakfast, lunch, dinner, and drinks!

See Komodo Dragons at the Honolulu Zoo, just an 8-minute walk away, or visit indoor and outdoor tropical exhibits at the Waikiki Aquarium, less than a mile away.

For studio snacks, head to the Waikiki Farmers Market at the Hyatt Regenc
host_about: Aloha my name is Peter.  I was born and raised on Oahu and went to college in Oregon.  I always had Hawaii in my heart and couldn't wait to move back home! Now that I have a family I wanted to start a vacation rental to help pay for my children's daycare while also providing visitors an affordable vacation rental with an excellent location to enjoy this island that I love. It is so rewarding when I hear about how much people enjoyed their stay on Oahu and how much they loved their stay in our condo.

name: Jeflani Hawaiian Retreat
host_about: We are a couple who enjoy spending time in the two greatest states the USA has to offer, Colorado and Hawaii. Our lifestyle has become one of greater leisure which provides us the opportunity to enjoy the outdoor activities unique to each of these states; you cannot snorkel among reefs in Colorado, and you cannot enjoy a great day of downhill skiing in Hawaii. We get to do both. Hoping you enjoy our Hawaiian Retreat as much as we do.

name: Ocean view !! The  best location in waikiki!
Kona Plumeria Guesthouse
neighborhood_overview: The property is well located, within walking distance to the beach and within minutes of shopping and restaurants, including a grocery stores and farmers markets.
host_about: I've lived in Hawaii for 15 years. I adore our island home and creating beautiful spaces. We would love to host you!

name: The Jungle Getaway
neighborhood_overview: Beautiful peaceful neighborhood with nice quiet streets for strolling, ocean views and the lovely Ainaola Park less than 5 minutes away.

host_about: We are a family of five living in the beautiful state of Hawaii! We love outdoor living and you will often find us at the beach surfing or up in the mountains hiking.

name: Rainbows in Paradise Ocean & Mountain  views  24/7

31st floor Waikiki condo for 2 - walk to the beach
host_about: My wife and I love to travel and the best part of traveling is the people we meet. By acquiring rental properties in Waikiki, we are able to meet people with diverse backgrounds from different parts of the world.

name: Island Paradise Inn - Aloha Suite
neighborhood_overview: Pahoa Village is a quaint little town on the southeastern side of The Big Island of Hawaii. This is in the lush, green Puna region of the island, where there are fewer tourist traps and more of the “old” Hawaii of yesteryear. Pahoa has wooden sidewalks and storefronts dating back 100 years, and is a town time seems to have forgotten. Tourists are delighted with Pahoa's fine restaurants, including Thai, Mexican, Chinese and Tuscany Italian... some of the best on the island! There are funky little shops and restaurants, a Sunday farmer's market featuring live music and fresh local fruits and vegetables. And Pahoa is home to the Akebono Theater, which is the oldest in the state! The village of Pahoa is situated in the middle of some of the most beautiful, tropical surroundings, near Kehena Beach which has snorkeling, swimming, surfing and beachcombing. There are lots of unbelievably beautiful crystal clear tide pools to explore and a thermal “hot” pond along with the free black sand beach
host_about: Aloha my name is Ophelia. Although I'm Armenian,  I've lived in Hawaii almost all my life. My son and I and my brother operate the Island Paradise. Inn and Boogie Boogie Pizza (best pizza ever

name: Lava Lookout: Nāmaka  / full equipped kitchen /
neighborhood_overview:
Kalapana is unique. Come visit the magic of a 30 year old lava flow. Even if the lava isn't flowing, this is definitely one of the most unique places on earth. Pahoa, a super awesome little village is 20 minutes away - or run to Uncle Roberts for the stop and shop or nightly night market on Wednesdays (not to be explained - just to be experienced :)).

Update: Lava changes daily. The most recent lava flow has slowed, but has not been declared over yet. We ask for your understanding of our community during these Lava flow fluctuations. Ocean views and Mountain views. Quiet Isolated Lava life for all adventures and travelers. Please stay informed and updated on all lava conditions before traveling to Kalapana. Kokua. Take Care. Aloha.

host_about: I'm a athlete that travels often and welcome people from all over the world in our beautiful island to share our Aloha spirit!!!

name: 3 blocks to Turtle beach and Ali'i Dr
host_about:
Larry and I and our 2 Schnauzers moved from Oregon to Kona 10years ago. One of us LOVES to fish and enjoys the calm blue waters of Hawaii (and one of us doesn't). 
Our neighborhood has kept it's Hawaiian feel and is a nice mix of cultures. Just 3 blocks from Da Poke Shack and Turtle and Banyan Beaches, which are on Ali'i drive (part of the Ironman marathon). We are also jogging distance to White Sands Beach, a favorite for boogie boarding.

name: Spacious Treehouse Studio
neighborhood_overview:
Lush green hillsides and a possible visit by a wild rooster, goat, or cow. It's the perfect getaway from the bustling tourist towns and still conveniently located near many recreational areas. Our favorite white sandy beach is a short 10 minute drive north.

This well-established neighborhood is a mix of residential and agricultural land. Our neighbors are a combination of multi-generational households, young local families and mainland transplants like us. It's a live-and-let-live kind of place that we've called home for 15+ years.

I'll mention again here because of a guest complaint, some of our neighbors keep roosters that get up early.
host_about: I'm born and raised in the San Francisco Bay Area, transplanted to Oahu 20 years ago. Some of my favorite things about Hawaii are the people both Kanaka (those of Hawaiian descent) and Kama`aina (long-time resident), the natural beauty, the FOOD and of course the Aloha Spirit!

name: DORMITORY STYLE
neighborhood_overview: We love that we live in one of the most beautiful places on Earth. Known as the "7 Mile Miracle," the North Shore of Oahu is one of the most sought after places for vacationers. We're lucky enough not only to live steps away from world class beaches, surf breaks, and historic Haleiwa town, but we are a serene getaway amongst all of it.
host_about: Aloha! I am the proprietor of a private lodging on the North Shore of Oah'u, a place where you will find an escape from the everyday, relaxation, and some of the most beautiful beaches in the world. Here at my home you enjoy the beautiful weather, lush jungle surroundings, and the way the sunlight glistens off the Pacific.

name: Comfortable Place at Pepeekeo with a View 2.
host_about: I used to be a farmer and grew banana for the people. Currently, I am a tour guide as a part-time job.

name: Honokaa Private bedroom on Main Strip of town!
neighborhood_overview: It's in the Historic town of Honokaa, you get to enjoy walking to town, to farmers markets, shops, restaurants, historic theatre for only $6, free public pools, skate park, libary next door. My Shave ice and boba tea shop in front!
host_about: I'm an entrepreneur, and best selling author. In my spare time I often mentor and do inspirational speeches for young entrepreneurs, to inspire them to follow their dreams. I love to tahitian dance, surf, spearfish, hike, and martial arts!

name: Lovely Space
host_about: I like to travel alone and stay in safe, comfortable environments, but hate hotels.  Perhaps you have a lovely place to host me as I make my way and explore.....I like to bicycle, hike, dance tango, and do yoga.  I speak a bit of french.  I love to cook, and to share food with friends.   I have a serious job, so try to be very un-serious when not working.

name: Cozy cabin near Volcano National Park
Rainbow Jo Inn,  Queen’s Loft
neighborhood_overview: Rainbow Jo Inn is located in the heart of downtown Hilo, one block from bay front.  It is a $20 cab ride from the Hilo airport and one block from the Hilo bus terminal.
host_about:
I am the owner and designer of Rainbow Jo clothing.  You can find my original design dresses, skirts, tops in fine boutiques throughout the islands.
We also have Men’s and boy’s Aloha shirts and girls dresses too !
My flagship store is in downtown Hilo
And the Queen’s loft is upstairs and the Sunflower room is downstairs in the Rainbow Jo building. So you can Shop and drop right here.

name: Charming Studio with King Bed Private Bath - Ac
Makaha Beach front Cabanas
neighborhood_overview:
The beautiful unspoiled roustic west side of Oahu hosts some of the best trails, nature conservation lands, fishing, and beaches in the state.

Enjoy Oahu in its early heydays before overdevelopment occurred.

Experience the Aloha and Power of Nature in the unspoiled beauty of Waianae.

name: Private Manana Home central to all sides of Oahu
neighborhood_overview: The private guest suite/studio is attached to the main home.  Guests have their own private entry to the studio.  The home is located up the hills of Pearl City.  It is close to the tropical rainforests and hiking trails with a waterfall at the end of the hike.  It is a walking distance to a gas station with a convenience store, a local food drive-inn and shaved iced.  It is also centrally located without traffic:  20 minute drive to Pearl Harbor/Hickam base and the Honolulu Airport, 30 minutes to Waikiki, and 25 minutes to Koolina, 45 minutes to the North Shore.  We are much closer to the Honolulu Airport, Downtown and Waikiki compared to Waipahu, Ewa Beach, Mililani, Kapolei, Makaha and Wahiawa.  So sitting in Honolulu traffic isn’t as bad as the other cities mentioned... so choose us!

name: My Sweet Ohana
host_about: We welcome you to the Big Island of Hawai'i to embrace the spirit of Aloha (Love) that extends beyond the island adventures into a beautiful and serene space where you can tap into yoga, music and other explorative and meditative practices. We are a passionate, creative and fun loving family, who are committed to giving our guests a deep, friendly, open minded and heart centered experience. After living in New York and traveling the world for over 25 years we decided to set some strong roots together here on the Big Island of Hawai’i where we felt our heavenly oasis close to the ocean as a great place to start! Where enchantment and exploration meet and provide great ‘lookout’ points and beautiful scenic views at the edge of the cliffs of lava. We look forward to sharing the powerful 'mana' (healing life force energy) of this ancient landscape with you soon; on an epic journey to live our lives more abundantly day by day with 'pono' (consciousness) in our hearts! Mahalo Ke Akua (with gratitude to the creator of this life). read less

name: Hale Ho’omaha
neighborhood_overview: The neighborhood is friendly.

name: Charming Hawaiian Hale (A/C, WiFi) 30 day
neighborhood_overview:
Windward Mall, Safeway, Starbucks, CVS, Walgreens, Subway, and many other eating establishments are within 1 block of our home.

Windward Mall has a wonderful farmer’s market on Wednesdays and Sundays.

Kailua also has a great farmer’s market on Thursday evenings.
host_about:
I am a nurse at a local hospital on Oahu. I enjoy spending time with my husband, Gen, and children, Madison and Brandon.

We love to travel.  We also enjoy meeting new people, having new travel experiences and trying new things.

name: Palm Tree Room rm# 2 Kaimuki,Kapahulu,Diamond Head
neighborhood_overview:
Waikiki is on strike! so if you want quiet and peaceful place to stay book my Airbnb asap before it all booked up.

This house is situated in an awesome well establish middle class neighborhood. It is near a lot of great restaurants, stores and centrally located to town and other main attractions. There is public transportation via The Bus around the corner on 6th ave. There is 2 car parking out front of the house or across the street. We are near Diamond head, KCC, University of Hawaii, Monsarrat street, Waikiki is 10 min away and the airport depending on traffic is about 25 min drive. neighborhood_overview:
This is a rural setting. Please grocery shop in Hilo or Waimea BEFORE coming to the house.

We are easily accessible by car to all the Big Island attractions such as Downtown Hilo (15 minute drive) Volcanoes National Park (1 hour South), Waipio Valley (1 hour North), and the countless sights and adventures along the Hamakua Coast, the Hamakua House is the perfect location to base your Big Island adventure vacation. The legendary Akaka Falls State Park is only 4 miles away from the Hamakua House. Onomea Bay is only 4 miles away, which is the home of the Hawaii Botanical Gardens. It is an unforgettable drive to get there and the bay is a wonderful place to have a picnic. We are only 1 mile (easily walkable) from the quaint main street of Honomu, HI. This town was established in the sugar cane plantation era and remains today boasting some wonderful gift shops, two restaurants, a coffee house, and the Island's best Zip Line Tours.

name: Tropical Zen Bungalow - Private Garden Oasis
neighborhood_overview:
Kehena Beach: (1.5 miles way) a stunning black sand beach (clothing optional). On the right day, you might have the opportunity to swim with the dolphins that frequent the coastline.
Red Road: Kalapana-Kapoho Beach road, You can now drive down the 'Red Road' for about 9 miles and enjoy the magical tree tunnels and ocean view lookouts along one of Hawaii's most beautiful coastal routes. Parking is available where the road ends at Pohoiki Beach Park which narrowly escaped the lava flow in 2018. Catch stunning views of the black lava cliffs on your drive to Pohoiki oceanfront park. There you can soak in naturally heated ponds or sunbathe on the newest black sand beach in the world.
Uncle Robert's Awa Bar and Farmers Market: Uncle Robert's is a must see weekly event on Wednesday nights. Uncle Robert's offers local, live Hawaiian music, dancing, delicious food vendors, fruits and vegetable stands, and unique local craft vendors (4 miles).
Pahoa town is a 20 minute drive. The

host_about:
Aloha Mai Kākou (Love To All)! 
My sister and I are proud kānaka ʻōiwi (Native Hawaiians). We were born and raised in these Islands.
The only thing we love more than our culture is sharing it with others! It'd be our pleasure to host all walks of life and show you the true Aloha of these Islands. When you stay with us, you become a part of our 'Ohana (Family). We can't wait to meet you!
Me ke aloha pumehana (With warm regards), Anolani & Noelani 

When my sister and I are not hosting, we are either going to the beach, hiking, traveling, or studying! We both work as medical professionals and attend classes at the University of Hawaii: Mānoa. We believe the most important thing to take from our travels are memories and knowledge of cultures, not souvenirs."The world is a book, and those who do not travel read only a page." - Saint Augustine

name: Hidden Paradise in Hawaii
neighborhood_overview:
Only 15 minutes from Laupāhoehoe point beach park. Less than 10 minutes from Papaaloa Country Store. 25 minutes from Hilo.

Our favorite things to see, things to do, and places to eat:

Going north (turning left out of our driveway) there is Papa’aloa country store less than 10 minutes away that is really worth going to. You can buy most necessities there and some nostalgic fun stuff, but they also prepare fantastic food in the back and have a little restaurant as well. They have live entertainment sometimes on weekends. Turn left out of our driveway, go around the first big gulch and then watch for the sign. there is a road angling off to the right that takes you straight to it.

Laupahoehoe Beach Park is only a little further past Papaaloa. Go around the second big gulch and turn right, follow the windy road all the way down to the point. You can picnic there, play ball and swim. Fantastic views as well and learn about the devastation of the tsunami t

neighborhood_overview: The neighborhood is a highly desirable area within Hawaii Kai.  Quiet and safe, it is a pleasant area for taking walks and exploring. Views  of Koko Crater as well as the marina from water front lots exist along a stroll of the neighborhood.  Sandy Beach Park is 1.5 miles away. Hanauma Bay is 1.7 miles away. Bellows Field Beach Park in Waimanalo is a wonderful white sand beach open on the weekend only starting at noon on Friday. 4.2 miles away, It is a more friendly beach for boogie boarding or just taking a nice long walk. name: Private Spacious Room on Sacred Land w Bathroom
neighborhood_overview: It's an absolutely breathtaking Jungle! If you could use a break from the city noises and pollution this might be what you are looking for! This area is a standard for the highest air quality in the world. It is called sunny Kapoho even though it's on the wetter side of the island.  Although COVID is still a worldly happening, there are still local art and music events happening throughout the week.  Ecstatic dances on Sundays and Thursdays are continuing in Hilo.  Open Mic every Monday at the Kava Bar, and Uncle Robert's every Saturday at Kalapana are still lively events .  Maku'u Farmers Market is loaded with local produce, crafts and more every Sunday.  Kehena Beach, Shipman's Beach, and a few local secret spots are still open to visit for a swim or snorkel. This is authentic Hawaii, an area where time can stand still. There is little to no traffic, very few homes on the coast, canopied trees over the road opening into crashing waves on the black lava! Breathtaking!! Our sweet town
host_about: Gray and I are so grateful to be stewards of this magical land! We love to do our best to create a wonderful experience for our guests.  Looking forward to meeting you and sharing the beauty, peace and calm of this land with you.  We love to start our day with a quiet walk in the jungle and our way back gather produce from our neighborhood fruit stands.  We enjoy the quiet laid back vibe we have on this side of the island and one of the cleanest airs on the planet!   Our favorite part of this property is all the fruit trees and the plush landscape !

host_about: Easygoing, well-travelled European that traded the old world for an island in the Pacific some 20 years ago. Enjoys coffee, conversations, a good book and interesting experiences.

name: Newly-Remodeled! Waikiki Apartment with Ocean View
Cargo Container HomeOnTheLava~ OceanView sleeps 4
neighborhood_overview: Guests can enjoy the peace and quite of God’s creation here in this place. You can also visit many of the major “tourist” sites within an hour of this home. Whether you want to see waterfalls, hike on old lava flow, visit a black sand beach or just have an amazing Wednesday night out at Uncle Robert’s this location is like no other.
host_about:
They say, “when you do what you love, you never work a day in your life.” Managing property and traveling through America’s coastal region has armed me with the experience necessary to provide you with a quality place to stay in some of the country’s most stunning locations. 

I have been a property manager and owner for 19 years. 30 years ago, I made Lantana my home, and I am proud to say it is still the great coastal town that I grew up loving. Whether you enjoy going to the beach, boating, shopping, or sampling the local fare, Lantana is the place to go - and stay a little while. 

I have also spent a lot of time on the Big Island of Hawaii, and like most, remain fascinated by all that it has to offer.  This was why I took on the adventure of converting shipping containers into off-grid vacation bungalows on the lava fields of Kalapana. It was an adventure I will never forget. These lush interiors are situated directly on the lava field and under a night sky lit by thousands of twinkling stars.  With the ocean as your view and Kilauea volcano in your backyard, it is truly a once in a lifetime experience you won’t soon forget. 

A hui hou,
Ron
Living a Joyful & Blessed Life

Stay in a historic farmhouse by Volcanoes Park
neighborhood_overview:
Auntie Malia's House is at the end of a narrow, quiet country lane in the heart of historic Volcano Village. A true community and village, this is a place where you can walk down the roads and seldom see a car, where neighbors all know each other and talk story with one another; where people love the precious endemic forest and bird life that surrounds us. This is the perfect place to get away from it all.

There is so much to see and do in Volcano! Every Sunday morning and Wednesday evening you can browse food and crafts at the Volcano Farmer's Market at Cooper Center. Volcanoes National Park is just 1-and-a-half miles away; you can even walk to the Park from Auntie Malia's. There are a number of quaint, unique shops and restaurants in Volcano Village, as well as Volcano Art Center, which features beautiful works by local artists and an interpretive rainforest walk. In the evening, take in one of the many events at Volcanoes National Park “In the Park After Dark” series, enj
host_about:
Originally from Maui, I am a local lady who was raised immersed in the traditional Hawaiian culture, lifestyle, and language. My passion is sharing the beauty and aloha of our Islands; in particular, I love to share my knowledge of our unique Hawaiian culture, history, and melodic language. 
I am a semi-retired archaeologist who loves to travel, and when I'm not living out of a suitcase, I enjoy hosting other travellers from around the world.

name: Anthurium Inn at Hale Nonno
neighborhood_overview:
Leilani Estates is a well established, quiet and safe neighborhood. Our lot is located towards the top of the neighborhood, which was untouched by the 2018 Kilauea lava flow (which ended in August, 2018)

It is a peaceful area perfect for strolling around in the day or for evening stargazing.

A 20 minute drive south has you on one of the most beautiful scenic drives on the Big Island, Puna’s Red Road. Along this coastal drive your senses will relish in the views, sounds and scents of crashing waves, surfing turtles, spinning dolphins and in the winter the majestic humpback whales.

Towering coconuts and other native trees crate a shimmering filtered light that seems to dance as you navigate along the slow twists and turns. This area is truly one of the most ✨ places on the island.

Heading North, less than 5 miles away is Historic Pahoa Village, which has excellent locally owned restaurants, a natural food store, grocery store and souveni
host_about:
Aloha, welcome to Hale Nonno~ 

Both Alden and I take great happiness in welcoming you to our cottage in Puna, Hawai’i.

We are both born and raised here on the Big Island and have chosen to stay throughout our adult lives. Alden and I have traveled to many countries, all the while seeking connections with the people and cultures of each location. 

As hosts, we welcome and invite you to come and experience Hawaii through the eyes of lifelong residents. Leilani Estates offers a place to unwind, relax and meld into the tropical landscape. 

There are countless reasons why Alden and I have chosen to make our lives here, however it is the island feeling and the spirit of Aloha that reminds us each day why we continue to call Hawaii our home.  Aloha and welcome ~

The ocean is always fun to watch and is particularly beautiful at the end of Beach Road to the south of Paradise Road about a mile from the house.

If you're interested in experiencing pristine Hawaii this is a great place to do it. My place offers the convenience of being only 10 minutes from the convenience store in Orchidland, 15 minutes from Keaau, with a grocery store and a bunch of other restaurants and shops, 25 minutes from Hilo and the airport, but also out in the country with the ocean waves audible from your room and very few neighbors. name: Sweet Spot - Treetop Tropical Home. Walk to Beach
neighborhood_overview:
Want to see what Hawaii was like 50 years ago? Then this is it. Out of the way and off the beaten path our side of the island is slow, slow but you can go, go with many places to see and visit for day trips. This neighborhood sports some of the finest coastal drives on the island with trees overhanging a windy narrow road creating tunnels of green with shards of sunlight breaking through the leaves. Stop at many places and soak up the waves as they crash against rocky shores and spray you with a salty mist. So many places that are photo-worthy.
On Saturday morning there is a local farmer's market down the road about four miles. Great place to grab local foods to eat there or bring back to cook.
On Sundays, there is a big drumming circle at the beach that carries over to the Seaview Lawn (also a walk away) into the later afternoon and early evening. Sundays from 7 a.m. to 2 p.m. is the Maku'u Market which has scores of food booths with a variety spanning the globe. Live musi
host_about: I have traveled to 47 countries and know what it means to find the right spot to recharge and inspire. I have homesteaded the Sweet Spot since 1991 and you can now enjoy the fruits of my labor both figuratively and literally as there are dozens of food-bearing trees on the property.

name: Aloha OM- A retreat in nature
neighborhood_overview:
Aloha Om is located in Orchidland Estates in Kea'au, HI. The air is cool and fresh at night you will want to have a cozy sweatshirt available especially while toasting marshmallows over the fire in the fire pit.

At night you will hear the frogs singing and in the morning the birds chirping. It is very peaceful yet close to town.

Orchidland Estates is an ideal location for exploring the east side of the Big Island. We are 40 minutes from Volcano National Park, 35 minutes to Kalapana and Uncle Robert's market, 15 minutes to Pahoa & Kea'au and 25 minutes to Hilo and the airport.

Maku'u farmers market on Sunday's is just down the hill. We are also an easy drive to Secret Falls, Akaka Falls, the Botanical Gardens and coastline on the east and Pele's freshest creations.

There is a convenience store and a gas station at the bottom of our hill. There are great farmers markets very close and food stores within 15 minutes drive as well.

I am so grateful for the hosts that open their lovely homes to us travelers! Much gratitude and blessings!  Life is for Living :)

name: Aloha Sanctuary
neighborhood_overview: We are located in Hawaiian Paradise Park, a large subdivision on a rugged east-facing coastline. A 15-minute walk or bike ride takes you to where the ocean meets lava cliffs. We are a short distance from fabulous outdoor markets:  Maku'u Market on Sundays 8am-2pm, or Kalapana on Saturdays from 8am-noon. Hilo has a market everyday downtown from 7am-3pm, with expanded vendors on Wednesdays and Saturdays. Volcanoes National Park is about an hour drive, and a must-see!  A 45 minute drive brings you to the most recent lava flow, and beautiful black sand beach of Pohoiki. The quaint town of Pahoa, 20 minutes away, offers great restaurants (try Pele's Kitchen for breakfast, Ning's or Kaleo's or Pahoa Fresh Fish for dinner), a few colorful boutiques, and Island Naturals or Malama Market for groceries. The town of Kea'au is 15 minutes away with grocery, drug, and hardware stores. The small town of Orchidland hosts a new more casual version of Kaleo's restaurant, open daily 8am-8pm. Hilo is a 25

name: Lava Lookout: Pakaʻa  - off grid suite
neighborhood_overview:
Kalapana is unique. Come visit the magic of a 30 year old lava flow. Even if the lava isn't flowing, this is definitely one of the most unique places on earth. Pahoa, a super awesome little village is 20 minutes away - or run to Uncle Roberts for the stop and shop or nightly night market on Wednesdays (not to be explained - just to be experienced :)).

Update: Lava changes daily. The most recent lava flow has slowed ended and there is currently no molten surface lava anywhere on the island. We ask for your sensitivity of our community during these Lava flow fluctuations. Ocean views and Mountain views. Quiet Isolated Lava life for all adventures and travelers. Kokua. Take Care. Aloha.
host_about:

I've seen much of the US (all 50 & PR) but am looking to explore much more of the world while making a positive impact on the environment, people and animals.

name: in Tahiti room
Moana View Suite private entrance and view
neighborhood_overview: Our home is located on six and a half acres with beautiful gardens. We have a unique stay for tents on the three acres below us we are working on. In the morning we have all types of birds singing good morning! On occasions mouflon sheep, wild pheasants and quail will make their way through the property in the early morning. The sunset view over the ocean is amazing, and star gazing is incredible! We suggest you don load SkyView Light app for star gazing. If you enjoy hiking there is Pohue Bay located right below us, Manuka park, local beaches, Kula Kia Caverns for a tour. The southern most point of the United States south Point is a short drive and on the way there is Mac nut, coffee tasting at a local farm with exotic bird too see. Also green sand beach  is located there, a three mile hike, If needed to hitch a ride some locals are available for cash only. We have a local farmers market on Fridays and Saturdays blocks  from our home, two grocery stores, gift shop, cafe, pizza and bak
host_about: I am a licensed cosmetologist of over 40 years in Washington and Hawaii. My hobbies are gardening, stain glass, cooking, riding my Harley. I am educated in being self efficient. name: •*•Your Private Suite in Paradise! •*•
neighborhood_overview: A very quiet and respectful residential community, the Kea’au Ag Lots is a very desirable living area and subdivision.  Please be respectful of our home.  Drive safely and slowly.  With that said, “E komo mai!” Welcome to our island home.  We are so glad to have you.  We are conveniently located 8 miles south of Hilo and 12 miles north of the Volcano National Park.  Less than a mile from our Hale Moana is the little town of Keaau.  You will find a 'Foodland' grocery store, CVS Longs Drug store, and a great little farmers market where you can delight yourself in the vibrant flavors of Hawaii's tropical fruits and local grown veggies.   A few of the restaurants you'll find in town , thai cuisine, Lemongrass Grille, and local-style plate lunch place called L&L.  Shipman public park has tennis courts, a basketball court, and a playground for kids.

name: Studio: Mele Ohana o Ahonui ("of Patience") Duplex
neighborhood_overview: Hawaiian Paradise Park, also referred to as Paradise Park and known by many as HPP, is a quiet neighborhood on the East side of the Island.  It is most known for it's beautiful cliffs and sunrises and it's convenient distances from Volcano, Hilo, the newest black sand beaches and much more!  Hawaiian Paradise Park is located around 20 minutes from the Hilo Airport.  It is in the heart of the lush green side of the Big Island of Hawaii.  At the bottom of the neighborhood are beautiful cliffs where you can hike or fish, right off of Beach road.  Shipman's beach is also at the bottom of the neighborhood, but requires an hour hike each way from the parking area.  To get there, take Kaloli Drive and drive to the end of the road and make a left.  Park your vehicle at the dead end.  See the Hawaiian Paradise Park Neighborhood Association's website for more information about the area.  Sometimes, when the volcano is active, you can see the lava glow from our neighborhood.

host_about:
We are a couple of little if not no dislikes about anything, anyone or any place. We are Business Entrepreneurs and we find ourselves at home most of the time. We love to cook. Harumi in particular is a great cook and can whip up a great meal in minutes from scratch. She can cook a variety of ethnic dishes from japanese, chinese, filipino, as well as american and european dishes. We love the outdoors, we spend much of our spare time doing things like surfing, hiking, golfing driving around the island. 

From time to time we would fly to neighboring islands on impulses. We do many things at the fly of our pants. We are always on the go, but always have time for each other and our guests. Dinner is our most important meal of the day, because it is a time where we all get to sit around the table, have a wonderful meal, give thanks to God and pretty much share how our day went.

If your like us, who love to eat and try new things you will be stoked to find that Hilo has many eateries! From sweet to savory downtown Hilo has it all- or you can venture across the street to McDonalds, open 24 hours every day lol!

name: A secluded gem in the middle of town
neighborhood_overview:
Palolo is where the locals live! We are close to everything fun, quaint and unique to the small town of Kaimuki, 10 minutes by car to Waikiki and the University of Hawaii. All of these places are bike-able from here and the bus is close by.

This is a unique location five minutes from the H-1 freeway and 2 minutes from the cute small town of Kaimuki where you will find multiple coffee shops, delicious restaurants, and a few boutiques. Despite being so close to all these amenities the home is situated away from the road where you have to cross a small bridge on foot to access the property.
host_about:
Hi! I'm Vanesa.  I love to travel, brew beer, throw dinner  parties  and share my little oasis in the back of Palolo Valley.  I work in the film business as a scenic artist and a set dresser and have a very unpredictable life.  Everything I do is last minute and spontaneous and I like it that way.  As your host I am  there for you as much as you need me to be, even if I am away on business or adventure.  

As a guest in your space, you will probably not see me too much.  I am always out and about seeking local food & beer, scenery and adventure.   I make the most out of my time away from home as I am a former east coaster/new yorker living on tiny  island in the middle of the pacific. 

Why am I renting my  space on Airbnb? To fund my travel urges.  All proceeds from AIrbnb go to the travel fund.  With this in mind, I do my best to help you find what you need out of Hawaii- be it a night to crash after being out on the town, finding a home here somewhere, or squeezing the most out of a 3 day trip.  I welcome all your input for our future travels or how to make this space better.

name: Swim with the turtles, watch the whales.  RELAX.
neighborhood_overview:
Hilo is a laid back, funky historical town with a slow pace. It is the real Hawaii where the Hawaiian culture and language are once again thriving. Tourists arrive by cruise ship, walk the main street and shop, and leave a few hours later. The rest of the time, family picnics are the main form of entertainment, along with local music, hula (catch Merry Monarch Festival in April), ocean canoeing and serving up traditional foods (48 kinds of poke at the KTA supermarket but go before they run out at 5:00 pm!. This is the tropical side of the island, the green side, and well, "green means rain". But don't worry. On the average day this means waking up to sun, clouds and a downpour in the afternoon, then back to sun again. You've just got to wait a bit for the sun to come around—or if you are craving sun and sand, drive over Saddle Road to the north beaches.

We are situated on the western edge of town, on the beach road that connects 4 or 5 marine parks. You can swim
host_about: I am from West Vancouver, B.C.  I work at Simon Fraser University as a professor of philosophy and neuroscience but despite that, I am actually quite a nice person. name: Farm Stay Jungalow W/ 180° Sunrise & Ocean Views
neighborhood_overview:
Papaaloa is a coastal community southeast of Weloka and northwest of Ninole on the Hamakua Coast. Like many of the neighboring villages along this eastern shoreline, Papaaloa was once an integral part of the sugar cane industry on the Big Island. The village has since evolved into quiet neighborhoods along the main highway and nearby side roads. A general store and post office are available in Papaaloa, and an airport, grocery stores, and other amenities are available in Hilo 18 miles south.

The sunrises along the Hamakua Coast are a wonder to behold, and Papaaloa is a great place for whale watching during certain months of the year. Streams run through Papaaloa, and the climate sustains lush rainforest and a wide range of vegetation and fruit trees. The region receives 120 inches of rainfall per year, and average temperatures range from the mid 60’s to 80’s Fahrenheit year-round.

Location, Location, Location! We are in the middle of it all.

Watch the sunsets from nearly any vantage point along the beach and see the Friday night fireworks from the Hilton Hawaiian Village. The nearby neighborhood includes several major hotels and numerous large and small restaurants and nightclubs that cater to every nationality. Ask the kama'aina (locals) for their tips. The Royal Hawaiian Shopping Center and other “World Class Shopping” may be found on Kalakaua Avenue (the street fronting the beach). name: The Ohana
neighborhood_overview:
The neighborhood is country style Hawai'i. Preserved Hawai'i, that is unincorporated. Neighbors are friendly though they appreciate their privacy and not to be disturbed by tourism. Lay low and enjoy the Hawai'i lifestyle here.
Around 7:00 am you might hear the chickens from surrounding neighbors. I don't own any chickens so it is quite peaceful. My place is hugged by 2600 acres of Hawai'i state land. We are on our own little corner of the island. The Hawaiians valued the sense of seclusion and an abundance in space. The homes here are built with that tradition of "not being able to see another person's house in your view. This is why in this area things are so "far away" than what you may be use to living on a mainland country. A new perspective to absorb!
host_about:
Aloha, I’m Linda. I travel the world for fun. I am grateful for the Airbnb community and all its kind hosts that have made seeing the world more affordable, comfortable, and safe. 
And how I have been able to open my home to world travelers and share the love for the island of Hawai’i. I value seeing the world in an unincorporated way and truly feeling connected to the cultural energy every place gives us. 

I’m a friendly chipper person who loves to garden, yoga, ocean, and live a healthy fulfilling life.

neighborhood_overview:
- This is an older, quiet, residential neighborhood with not much going on. Very quiet, safe, and lots of street parking. We park on the street and leave the secured driveway open for guests. Please remember to close the gate.

- This is not a party house, we respect the `āina (land), local culture and native peoples. All guests must have a shared respect for the Islands and the people.

- There are dogs nearby, and one on the property.

- The solar heating may not produce extremely hot water on overcast days.

- There is protocol for trash disposal and food waste. Everything should be in an enclosed plastic bag before placing in the outside bins. Food waste especially, must be wrapped securely. All recyclables must be cleaned completely before throwing out.

- Being on a tropical island, there are many bugs and critters in the neighborhood.

- `Aiea is located in the center of the Island, allowing for explorations in a timel
host_about: SUP surfer, physical comedian, dancer, actor, writer, yogi, dog--cat loving snowboarder who has appeared on Broadway. Home-grown in Hawai'i, and spent many years in NYC. I have an MFA in Writing and Acting from the New School in NYC, have taught at NYU. I do Yamuna body work to align the skeletal system, love eating organic fruits and vegetables and being in the ocean at dawn. Respect for the `aina (land) and local people is needed to stay here.

name: Hale Nalu Sleeps 4, 3-Split ACs & Beach Access
neighborhood_overview:
The BEACH, Tamura's Market, Longs/CVS, Papa Ole's, North Shore Tacos, US Post Office, Medical Clinic, Prime Rib Truck, Korean BBQ and the Polynesian Convenience Store are ALL within walking distance.
Laie, Polynesian Cultural Center, Kahuku, Malaekahana and Turtle Bay are minutes away and the Sunset Beach on the North Shore around 20-25 minutes from the Hale.
Drive further to the Banzai Pipeline, Waimea Bay and then into historic Haleiwa Town. Visit Mokuleia Beach and hike around Kaena Point. The possibilities are endless. Drive around the island and visit Ko'Olina, the West side, the outlets in Waikele, Ka Makana Alii Shopping Center and venture into town for Ala Moana Center, Waikiki, Kakaako & the hikes in Diamond Head and Koko Head. Memorable place such as Punchbowl Cemetary and Pearl Harbor are not far off the beaten path.
host_about:
My husband I have worked tirelessly to  achieve and never forget where we have come from. I was once a homeless couch surfer and he came from a privileged family, yet humble and kind as can be. We met in the most unlikely place in the middle of Hawaii and have been with each other ever since. We own the real estate, however, I am the management team of the properties. This has become my full-time career along with the crazy restaurant in Hawaii. I put in 120% energy when embarking on a purchase of real property and converting into the ultimate vacation or long term rental experience. Yes, I do both. I grew up in the world of hospitality on the Islands of Maui and Oahu. I have eaten, resided and worked with all demographics. I love to travel and have stayed in my fair share of short term rentals that were never meant to be advertised as such. I used this as education and the inspiration to start one of my most successful ventures in my life. I know what I am truly passionate about. The pandemic was a two fold lesson and I am learning to embrace the change everyday. I hope you enjoy the mountain house or the hale in Hawaii as much as we do. It is the fruit of my hard work to read the honest review of another human who, recognizes how much effort was put forth.
I would love to invite anyone, who reads to the end of this story, a complimentary item or discount to their Experience Activity in Hawaii, a new form of business we decided to partner with Airbnb with.  The Surf and Bento package Experience is live. Please stay tuned on canoe rides, VIP tours and lei creation classes. We are bringing back the vintage world. 
Kim

Surfing, swimming, fishing, beach, waterfalls, ziplining are all short drives away.

name: Luxury Condo A215 at Molokai Shores Awaits You!

Check out the Saturday morning Market downtown where you can get fresh and locally grown produce and souvenirs.  Kaunakakai has two stores to purchase groceries. Experience the Molokai Hot Bread after 7:30pm from Kanemitsu's Bakery. Go exploring to the nearby beaches or Kaunakakai Harbor where you can swim, snorkel, or kayak. Play a round of golf at the IronWood Hills Golf Course. Reserve your unforgettable trip to the old leper colony at Kalaupapa. Take a tour of the plumeria farm. Hike to waterfalls... There is so much to do on this little island! This is also the best island to Relax!

name: Inn on the Park studio 15F, Clean & Cozy
Waikiki Inn On The Park 15F, Cozy & Clean
Gardenia studio
neighborhood_overview: Although there’s no side walk in front of the property, there is a newly installed sidewalk a short distance from the  house that pretty much takes right by the UHH and all the way downtown Hilo.
host_about:
Aloha!
A little about myself; 
I moved to the Big Island in 1993 from Guam after serving a short stint in the USCG during the Golf War,  then worked as an acute care nurse at our local Hilo hospital for the last 22 years.  

Ive remained mesmerized by this island’s amazing natural beauty, diverse ecosystems, terrains, and love the laid back lifestyle it provides which easily translated into me transforming my house to one I can happily and proudly share with those seeking to explore and experience this amazing island in a relaxed home setting.  

I'm originally  from the Micronesian Island of Yap,  known for its pristine water, manta ray dives ( check out the world-famous  Yap Divers ) and  its colorful and spirited bamboo war dance performed by bare chested natives in lion clothes and grass skirts, something I grew up doing.   
I embrace  cultural diversity and truly enjoy meeting people from all walks of life and all regions in the world.  I take pride in my house and the service that I provide my guests. I value my precious 'free' time by sneaking in sporadic reading here and there  and enjoying the outdoors; camping, hiking, swimming, kayaking, paddle board, and gardening, but most of all, I love traveling and looking forward to seeing a lot more of this amazing world we live in and experience different cultures along the way.

I’m always striving for a balanced lifestyle; healthy living through heath conscious cooking utilizing locally grown, ( a lot are my own home grown) produce, keeping physically active, and inner peace and serenity.   

I look forward to meeting you and I'm excited to host another amazing adventurous soul seeking to experience the Big Island of Hawaii!  

Welcome & E Komo Mai!

Diana

name: Come Hug A Pony
neighborhood_overview:
While only 10 miles to Hilo, the farm/ranch is located such that day expeditions can be taken to any part of the Island. Near by tourist destinations include the beaches at Hilo, Volcanos National Park, lower Puna where the recent lava flows have occurred and warm ponds created (great to relax in), Panaewa Zoo, Akaka Falls and Ranbow Falls; all within 25 miles.

Locally there are quite a few farmers markets, the Hilo Farmer’s Market and the Makuu Farmer’s Market are the larger ones, both approximately 10 miles away.

A neighbor has a sustainable living farm/ranch school where various activities are made available to the general public from time to time. And of course you are welcome to join the hosts on their lanai for refreshments or BBQ

name: Stunning Ocean view Hawaiian condo
neighborhood_overview:
Welcome to Molokai, The Most Hawaiian Island, where the aloha spirit flourishes and nature takes center stage. With vast expanses of empty beaches, miles of hiking trails, and open spaces, Molokai is a true paradise for nature lovers. You won't find any buildings taller than a palm tree here, and ALOHA is not just a word, it's a way of life.

One of the longest white sand beaches in Hawaii can be found here, and you might just have it all to yourself. There's so little automobile traffic that there's not a single traffic light. No malls, no elevators, and no neon. Burger wars? Not here.

Shop in small, friendly businesses in Kaunakakai, the largest town, and in the villages of Kualapuu and Kumu, where local markets offer fresh produce and homemade goods. Life here is slow and relaxed, rural and peaceful. It's like stepping back in time 50 years. Come experience the magic of Molokai, a place like no other.
host_about: Aloha and welcome to the paradise!

neighborhood_overview:
The walk or drive on government beach road from our driveway in either direction is beautiful and definitely an experience you won't forget!

If you are taking a left to Pahoa you'll see the newest 2018 lava flow and if your heading right you'll drive through the jungle and pass by the ocean! It is one of the most scenic routes on the whole island! A must to see!

There is more information in our listing on Getting Around for things to do and see!
host_about:
Aloha!!! My husband Andrew and I moved from Northern California to the Big Island of Hawaii in June 2014 to begin our dream on 3 acres in the jungle!!

We married in February on our property and started our Gecko Hideaway Airbnb in October 2015. In 2016 we had our handsome baby boy Kameron and in 2019 we had our beautiful baby girl Leila! We also love our fur babies! Our dogs names are Kaya and Nala, both sweethearts! Kona, Mira, Coco, and Cali are our kitties and don't be surprised if Kona decides to visit! The only thing we kindly ask is please no animals in the cabin in regards to allergies for any upcoming guests.

We love what we do!! Being self-sufficient in this amazing place is the greatest feeling and to share it with others is even better! We love the outdoors, of course our pets and most importantly our friends and family!

neighborhood_overview: Please know that this is a rural neighborhood.  All the homes in Hawaiian Paradise Park are sitting on one acre lots, so the blocks are long. Many lots have been cleared, but some are very wild and overgrown. Streets may be unpaved, as ours is, and there is no sidewalk.  There are no street lights and it can be very dark at night.  It is a quiet neighborhood. A great place to relax and listen to the birds. There is plenty of lush green trees and fragrant Island flowers blooming throughout the year.  It is a minimum of 10 minutes drive to the nearest market or gas station.  Nothing is "walk able," so please plan accordingly.
host_about: My husband Jeff and I are often called "down to earth" people.  We are kind and generous, compassionate and considerate; soft spoken, but energetic and fun-loving.  We are living in Keaau, Hawaii and are having the time of our lives!  As both parents and grandparents, we value family bonds and believe that relationships are our most valuable asset. We enjoy living simply, taking delight in listening to the birds, or catching a falling star in the night sky.

name: The Westin Nanea Ocean Villas - 1BR Villa
neighborhood_overview: Thrive on Hawaii's second largest island. The Westin Nanea Ocean Villas, Ka'anapali is a lively vacation ownership beach resort located in Lahaina, once the royal capital of Maui Loa. Balance historic museum tours with rain forest hikes to 400-foot waterfalls. Peer down a dormant volcano or snorkel The Forbidden Coast for unspoiled coral reefs. On your return, visit our sister property's Spa Helani, voted Top 10 Favorite Getaway Spas in the World by SpaFinder's 2010 Readers' Choice Awards. For a debriefing on local Lahaina legends, visit Pu'uhonua O Nanea cultural center. Eat at Mauka Makai, lounge by a rejuvenating pool with island platforms or work out in our WestinWORKOUT Fitness Studio. Our beach resort even offers ukulele lessons, hula dances and Kona lobster straight from the fisherman's cage. When the sun sets behind the palms, sink into your Heavenly® Bed. Our all-villa resort rentals feature marble bathrooms, room service and beach views. Refresh, refuel and relax on your Laha

name: The Westin Ka'anapali Ocean - 1BR Villa
neighborhood_overview: Embrace a welcoming abundance of amenities at The Westin Ka'anapali Ocean Resort Villas. There are Westin touches that keep in harmony with Ka'anapali's rich culture. Enjoy two sparkling oceanfront refreshing pools with rock waterfalls and soothing whirlpool spas, three restaurants at the resort, and two on-site markets providing a range of sundries, snacks, and supplies. Outdoor gas grills are perfectly situated for sunset barbeques.
