host_about: My goal is to make sure you have the best experience possible. I am very attentive and prefer to have a quick call to answer all your questions. I work hard to make sure you’ll have a fabulous time. Beware of cheaper options… Bed Bugs are an epidemic in Hawaii and you’ll find most hosts lose interest after you’ve booked.

name: Exceptional 1-Bedroom Condo In The Heart Of Kihei
host_about:
Matthew exemplifies integrity, energy, hard work, and service in every detail of your real estate transaction. Matthew grew up in West Springfield, Massachusetts and is a first generation Portuguese American. An 18 year island resident, Matthew began his real estate career in Hawaii and has established his reputation for building relationships with his clientele along with his commitment to community service as avid volunteer with the Special Olympics. 

“A defining moment in my life was my first year as a volunteer in the Special Olympics. It was then that I realized that life is about paying it forward. I saw first-hand how influencing others could help bring the best results to unlocking people’s limitations to reach their full potential.” 

A family man who enjoys spoiling his two God children, Matthew is also an athlete by nature and sports enthusiast. In his downtime, you’ll find him enjoying the perks of island living; hiking, kayaking, stand up paddle boarding, golfing, quality time with friends and family. Even though he has settled thousands of miles away from his home town, you will still catch him cheering on his beloved Boston Celtics, Boston Bruins, Boston Red Sox and the New England Patriots. 

Matthew has built a solid foundation of successfully guiding local, national and multi-national clients with their real estate acquisitions on Maui. He specializes in applying his expertise and market knowledge to each transaction. Matthew’s portfolio of high-end residential sales include over $24 million dollars in career sales. 

Matthew flies the country to build strong relationships with his clientele and uses his experience and foresight to proactively address details before they become a problem. He works diligently for his clients and initiates communication in every detail of the transaction, from the first phone call all the way to close. 

Matthew displays the “Aloha Spirit” daily with his volunteer work, business and in life itself.

Aloha,

name: Stylish & Private 1BR Garden Suite Near Bay
neighborhood_overview:
Kaneohe is one of the last bastions of laid back, island living on Oahu and unique in that it is still super convenient to everything. The mountains and ocean views are uncluttered by highrises and, unlike “town-side Honolulu”, traffic is minimal. The Windward side is generally both cooler and greener than the south/town side of Oahu.

We are just a couple blocks from Kaneohe Bay access points from which you can launch a paddleboard or kayak. Quiet Kaneohe Beach park with a small playground and pier is close by. Memorable hiking and white sand beaches are within easy reach.

Windward Mall with Macys, movies and restaurants is 8 minutes away by car. The nearest of 3 nearby grocery stores is less than 5 minutes away. Starbucks is 6 minutes away. The "hidden gems" of Kualoa Ranch, Chinaman's Hat Beach and Waiahole Poi Factory are just 20 minutes up the road. Great hiking is nearby too, such as thePu'u Ma'eli'eli Trail. The Ho'omaluhia Botanical park's lush 40 acres w
host_about: We're Sonya and Jordan Seng. Sonya is an Oahu kama'aina and Jordan is a California native. We met in college, and lived in Northern California, Chicago and the Boston area before returning to Hawaii  to raise our family.  We have 2 kids, 3 dogs and 2 cats and pastor a local faith community. We like strong coffee, dark beer, music and sailing. Enjoy a true Hawaiian Experience by visiting Volcano National Park, where you’ll spot live lava flows, lava tubes and glowing creatures. Book a tour with Blue Hawaiian Helicopters to see the action from the sky

An array of additional attractions are just a short drive from your door, including Akaka Falls State Park, Rainbow Falls, Hawaii Tropical Botanical Garden and Stargazing at Mauna Kea Mountain.

For an evening out, grab a lite at local eatery favorites such as Pepe’s Kitchen, pineapples Restaurant or Kuhio Grill- Home of the famous 1lb Laulau.

Kaimu Saturday Market is OPEN for business from 8-12pm & you’ll find lots of food vendors, fresh produce & music :) there. Kalapana has a small grocery store, a smoothie shack, a vegan café, bar, local Hawaiian food, and a local art gallery. The gorgeous Kaimu Beach is a short walk out over the lava field that was formed in 1990.
The fun little town of Pahoa is only nine miles away and has everything you will need. From the local natural food store, grocery store, drugstore, bakery, cafes, bars and restaurants to unique giftshops, art galleries, museum, community center and library.
Also, the Maku’u Farmers Market takes place right outside of Pahoa every Sunday from 8-2pm, produce, art, and food vendors from all over

name: "Puna Tiki", clean, private bath, entry, &parking
neighborhood_overview: Nanawale Estates is just this side of a rural neighborhood. Some of the roads are paved and some are not. Some of the gravel roads do have puddles but the main roads to this house are largely paved with a short ride from them to the house. It's quiet but sometimes the Hawaiian wildlife like to make their presence known, bird song can get pretty lively! The chickens are feral here so you may see an occasional flock here and there adding to the sounds of the jungle. The butterflies and giant moths are amazing and geckos abound! You will be very close to the jungle so you will see things you may not have seen before so expect jungle friends as we live within their environment and take measures to keep them outside, sometimes they will still appear. Welcome to the tropics!

neighborhood_overview:
Wai'anae is located approximately 28 miles (40-60 minutes depending on rush hour traffic) west of Daniel K. Inouye International Airport on the Leeward Coast, or the west side of the island. Wai'anae is a city in Honolulu County on the island of 'Oahu with a population of approximately 13,000, 80% being Native Hawaiian, Pacific Islander, or two or more ethnicities. A quick 15-minute drive without traffic to Ko'Olina Resort beach lagoons, Paradise Cove Luau, and Ko'Olina's PGA Golf Course.

Wai'anae is a close-knit community, and hometown to familiar faces such as actor Jason Momoa, MMA fighter Max Holloway, and Influencer Bretman Rock. This town is the countryside with a feel for old Hawai'i, the truly local impression offering some of the most beautiful beaches on the island, largest pod of spinner dolphins on the coastline, and beautiful sunsets. Though, like all beautiful places where everyone wants to be, we do experience traffic. The rush hour begins at 3:00pm going int

neighborhood_overview:
Wai'anae is located approximately 28 miles (40-60 minutes depending on rush hour traffic) west of Daniel K. Inouye International Airport on the Leeward Coast, or the west side of the island. Wai'anae is a city in Honolulu County on the island of 'Oahu with a population of approximately 13,000, 80% being Native Hawaiian, Pacific Islander, or two or more ethnicities. A quick 15-minute drive without traffic to Ko'Olina Resort beach lagoons, Paradise Cove Luau, and Ko'Olina's PGA Golf Course.

Wai'anae is a close-knit community, and hometown to familiar faces such as actor Jason Momoa, MMA fighter Max Holloway, and Influencer Bretman Rock. This town is the countryside with a feel for old Hawai'i, the truly local impression offering some of the most beautiful beaches on the island, largest pod of spinner dolphins on the coastline, and beautiful sunsets. neighborhood_overview: Ocean View is a historical rocky lava flow area filled with scattered green oases. A rural 'wild west' vibe and feel of the "real" Big Island. The house is surrounded by incredibly resourceful and kind neighbors. Our neighborhood watch is outstanding and it remains one of the safest places on the island. Sitting at approximately 4600 feet on the worlds largest volcano, the air is pristine and the weather is average of 75F in the day and 55F in the evenings. The bottom of the mountain offers two small grocery stores, amazing coffee café, gas, our favorite restaurant Tai Shai Farms, Ace Hardware, gift shop, secret access beaches, the rare Ka'u coffee farms, and a short trip to South Point and Green Sands Beach.

name: Upper house
neighborhood_overview:
The nearest medium sized town, Honoka'a is low key with some decent restaurants, we like to go to Harmoni Foods for Kim chi, bi bim bap, turmerick lemonade and kimchi grilled cheese. Catch a movie at the plantation era movie theater, Very nice skate park (really), grocery store and several places to vacation browse and buy local products such as chocolate, grass fed beef, flowers, crafts, etc.

Laupahoehoe point park, Kalopa park, Akaka Falls, The Hamakua coast, Hilo, Waimea, Waipi'o valley, are all accessible within a day from this comfy guest house.

White sandy beaches are 45 minutes from this spot. Further: Hawi about 70 minutes.

Hilo is a 50 minute to 1 hour scenic drive from here. And Volcano and Pahoa further on, about an hour and a half.

As a Host, I do my best to offer the same friendly, personalized service I have enjoyed in the past while using Air BNB. I really appreciate the local perspective when traveling. I will strive to bring that same level of service to you!

I enjoy facilitating your explorations around the Big Island, Hawaii. As someone who has been visiting the Big Island for years I am honored to be in a position to host travelers and visitors who are coming through to soak up the island's beauty. I will do my best to be a considerate, responsible, and courteous host.

I have travelled around the world over the years, from southeast Asia to the near east, and I have fallen totally in love with Hawaii and I am proud to call this place home. Cruising around the Big Island on the open roads is a great way to leave the mainland behind. 

I am more than happy to share  insights I have about life here, recommend restaurant favorites, and anything else that will allow your time here to be truly magical - Aloha

name: Kailani Hawaii-Modern Studio, feels like home
host_about:
Aloha,
I’m Linda. Hilo is my beloved hometown. I live here with my husband, raising our 8 year old son on the old-fashioned, yet beautiful Big Island of Hawaii. I love working as a tour guide since 2014, showing our wonderful island to visitors from all over the world. From my experience interacting with the visitors, I realized lots of them desired lodging with modern decorations yet maintaining an old Hawaiian feel. That’s exact what I aim to do when I was lucky enough to be able to open and host my first Airbnb. Kailani studio is my attempt to accommodate guests with a mix of modern and old Hawaiian flare. I hope to provide all my guests an old yet modern Hawaiian retreat after they tour our “time-forgotten”’east Hawaii, and provide the best customer services to make your day full of Aloha! 
Mahalo!
Linda

neighborhood_overview: Great studio located in Waikiki, just 2 blocks from the beach and 1 block from a modern gym. It is situated in an exceptionally well maintained Hawaiiana style building with nice gardens and a clean swimming pool. There is a resident manager on-site to oversee the maintenance and security of the building. There is community laundry on-site for your convenience. This unit comes fully furnished including all cookware, dishes, small kitchen appliances, linens and all utilities are included in the price. Perfectly located and central, you can enjoy all that Waikiki has to offer. There is a bus stop less than one minute away. NO PARKING IS PROVIDED. however, paid parking garages are nearby.
host_about: Aloha, Thank you for visiting my Airbnb List.  My name is David and I have lived in Honolulu for most of my life and I am excited you are planning to visit our islands. I worked as a tourist guide where I get the opportunity to show the stunning beauty of nature and rich Aloha culture to visitors come from all over the world. during my free time, I enjoy water activities, hiking, reading and traveling when I can.  if you book one of my listings, I will ensure you get all the information you needs about the island of Oahu. neighborhood_overview:
This is 14 unit building that represents Old Hawaii. Most of the residents, besides us, are older. They are very friendly and happy to chat and give recommendations. Great mix of people from the Mainland to Canada to Europe. The washer and dryer on the property are coin-operated and always available, but there are many laundry facilities within walking distance.

If you enjoy dining out, take some time and start trying every restaurant you come across and make your way through the street. You are bound to find a favorite. If there is a long line for certain places in the evening, try it during the day!

If you want coffee or need your quick essentials, there is the Island Country Store across from our location next door to the Ritz Carlton. There are close to 60 ABC Stores in our Waikiki, so you are bound to end up in one of those.

Just get out an explore, you’re in the heart of it all.

name: Kohola (Whale) Hut on Sacred Land
neighborhood_overview: There are local art and music events happening throughout the week. Ecstatic dances on Sundays and Thursdays are Pahoa and Hilo. Kehena Beach, Shipman's Beach, and a few local secret spots are still open to visit for a swim or snorkel. This is authentic Hawaii, an area where time can stand still. There is little to no traffic, very few homes on the coast, canopied trees over the road opening into crashing waves on the black lava!
host_about: Gray and I are so grateful to be stewards of this magical land! We love to do our best to create a wonderful experience for our guests. We enjoy the quiet laid back vibe we have on this side of the island and one of the cleanest airs on the planet!   Our favorite part of this property is all the fruit trees and the plush landscape !

name: Big Kahuna Cabin: Off Grid Bliss!
neighborhood_overview:
Our location offers the perfect blend of tranquility and convenience. While you'll feel a world away from the hustle and bustle, it's just a short 15-minute drive to the vibrant town of Pahoa. Explore its eclectic shops, indulge in local cuisine at charming restaurants, stock up on groceries, and catch live entertainment that captures the essence of the island spirit.

Nature enthusiasts will be thrilled to know that we are in close proximity to the renowned Volcano National Park. Immerse yourself in the dramatic volcanic landscapes, witness awe-inspiring lava flows, and embark on unforgettable hikes along the park's trails. The power and beauty of Pele, the Hawaiian volcano goddess, are tangible here.

Additionally, our location offers easy access to the famous black sands beach. Just a crow's flight away, this natural wonder beckons you to stroll along its shores, feel the warm sand between your toes, and witness the mesmerizing dance of the waves. It's a haven fo
host_about: Aloha! presently property manager at Da Coconut Farm at 14-276 Papaya Farms Road. Beautiful area with large old mango trees. Probably the cleanest air in the world coming directly from the east northeast 90% of the year. Beautiful unexplored aina both old and new, from recent lava formation. Looking forward to hosting you and your family.  My daughters and I will be your hosts. We look forward to providing you a safe and happy stay on our farm.

neighborhood_overview:
Ocean View is located nearly midway between Kailua-Kona and Hilo. Some businesses in this southern town include 3 gas stations, 2 grocery stores, an Ace Hardware store, and a few places to eat, including an excellent pizzeria/bakery.
Ocean View was developed in the 1950s by the Crawford Oil Company into 10,000+ 1 acre parcels and set up like a grid, where straight roads crisscross, starting from the highway at about 1,500’ elevation to the top, which is at about 5,000’. Manuka State Park borders the subdivision to the north and Kahuku National Park borders it to the south.

neighborhood_overview: Nanawale Estates is just this side of a rural neighborhood. Some of the roads are paved and some are not. Some of the gravel roads do have puddles but the main roads to this house are largely paved with a short ride from them to the house. It's quiet but sometimes the Hawaiian wildlife like to make their presence known, bird song can get pretty lively! The chickens are feral here so you may see an occasional flock here and there adding to the sounds of the jungle. The butterflies and giant moths are amazing and geckos abound! You will be very close to the jungle so you will see things you may not have seen before so expect jungle friends as we live within their environment and take measures to keep them outside, sometimes they will still appear. Welcome to the tropics!

name: Private Room w/ Shared Bathroom & Breakfast
neighborhood_overview: We are easily accessible to all the Big Island attractions such as Volcanoes National Park (1 hour South), Waipio Valley (1 hour North), and the countless sights and adventures along the Hamakua Coast, the Hamakua House is the perfect location to base your Big Island adventure vacation. The legendary Akaka Falls State Park is only 4 miles away from the Hamakua House.  Onomea Bay is only 4 miles away, which is the home of the Hawaii Botanical Gardens. It is an unforgettable drive to get there and the bay is a wonderful place to have a picnic. We are only 1 mile (easily walkable) from the quaint main street of Honomu, HI.  This town was established in the sugar cane plantation era and remains today boasting some wonderful gift shops, two restaurants, a coffee house, and the Island's best Zip Line Tours.

host_about: A tiki is a large or small wooden, pounamu or other stone carving in humanoid form, although this is a somewhat archaic usage in the Māori language. Hei-tiki are often considered taonga, especially if they are older and have been passed down throughout multiple generations. Carvings are often served to mark the boundaries of sacred or significant sites.   We hope to share our heritage & love for our sacred site with you at this retreat.

name: Papa'aloa Animal Lovers' Paradise #2
neighborhood_overview: This is an 11-acre farm/ranch, surrounded by similar properties.  The post office and store are just across the highway a short distance down the hillside.  There is a nearby gas station/convenience store and a beach park a very miles away.  There are other attractions and sight-seeing opportunities in both directions.
host_about:
I'm a single retired police detective from Oahu. For 16 years I offered horseback rides on Oahu, but moved to the Big Island with my horses when the ranch lease recently expired. 

Originally from the Midwest, I did a stint in the military, which brought me to the islands in 1978.  My education includes an AA in Foreign Languages, a BA in Psychology and completion of a Master's program in Guidance & Counseling. 
 
I'm a Christian, who believes the good Lord brought me to this fantastic place.
I love the serene beauty and quiet of this location, and since the house is much larger than one person needs, wish to share it with traveling guests,  who will also enjoy its comfort and fabulous views.  Besides that, the horses still "eat like horses", even though they are no longer earning their keep!

As a pet lover, I would prefer folks who also like animals.  Because I have so many, I don't have a chance to travel much, although in the past I did get the opportunity to visit Spain, France, Switzerland  and England.  I was stationed in Florida & CA as well as Hawaii while in the military.   

I enjoy a variety of books and movies, preferably well-written and thought-provoking.  A good comedy is always appreciated, as well.  My social life now is mostly a weekly ladies' luncheon and music nights at the Fifties Café.

name: Modern Kailua Studio: Your Peaceful Getaway
neighborhood_overview: Kailua is a serene coastal town on the eastern shore of Oahu, nestled beneath the majestic Ko'olau mountains. Despite being just a 30-minute drive from downtown Honolulu, Kailua maintains a distinct charm and atmosphere of its own. The town is renowned for its stunning beaches, particularly Kailua Beach and Lanikai Beach. Kailua Beach is known for its powdery soft white sand, calm turquoise waters, and being pet-friendly. It offers a variety of outdoor activities like swimming, kayaking, bodyboarding, kite surfing, and windsurfing.

host_about: A tiki is a large or small wooden, pounamu or other stone carving in humanoid form, although this is a somewhat archaic usage in the Māori language. Hei-tiki are often considered taonga, especially if they are older and have been passed down throughout multiple generations. Carvings are often served to mark the boundaries of sacred or significant sites.   We hope to share our heritage & love for our sacred site with you at this retreat.

neighborhood_overview: Located in the balmy, Southern part of Hawaii, The Big Island, is Mark Twain, a unique subdivision with narrow, gravel roads and few cars, where many pioneering women and men live in their own unique, free-style ways. A place where friendly people look out for each other. Your stroll through the neighborhood will feel like times gone by when nobody rushed, people greeted you, and traffic was rare. Lush tropical greenery and floral scents are plentiful within Mark Twain where the climate is perfect. It is usually sunny, with blue skies and a nice, little breeze during the day, and a bit of rain at night. You will be close to the pristine surf beach at Kawaa, where it is usually very quiet. There is a place in this area where you can fill up your bottle with spring-fed water flowing from the rocks.
host_about:
I moved to Hawaii in 1997 and have mainly focused on natural healing, organic gardening, and sustainability during those years. I have studied extensively with a Hawaiian medicine man and I have many tricks up my sleeve to resolve common chronic or acute health issues using plants, herbs and all kinds of natural remedies from nature. I am very passionate about helping people with their health.
I still love teaching Art and creating Art.

name: Beach Access & Sunsets at Kepuhi Beach Studio
neighborhood_overview: Step back into time at Kepuhi Beach Resort.  This complex was once an 18 hole golf resort hotel and spa destination for cruise ships and vacationers.  The neighborhood no longer wanted this type of experience on Moloka'i so the neighbors decided to block further resort development on some of the Island's most treasured and sacred land and beaches.  As a result the hotel pulled out and abandoned the golf course and hotel buildings, leaving the condo complex and pool to be locally owned and operated.  This is how the neighborhood likes it.  It's simple, quiet and peaceful.  Guests won't find full service golf resort and spa amenities, but they will find genuine healing, relaxation and restoration that comes from the natural beauty of Moloka'i, its beaches and its residents.  The neighbors are ready to embrace guests and help them as long as they are respectful and carry the spirit of Aloha with them.  As the locals say, "don't try to change Moloka'i, let Moloka'i change you."

name: The Westin Nanea Ocean Villas - 2BR Villa
neighborhood_overview: Thrive on Hawaii's second largest island. The Westin Nanea Ocean Villas, Ka'anapali is a lively vacation ownership beach resort located in Lahaina, once the royal capital of Maui Loa. Balance historic museum tours with rain forest hikes to 400-foot waterfalls. Peer down a dormant volcano or snorkel The Forbidden Coast for unspoiled coral reefs. On your return, visit our sister property's Spa Helani, voted Top 10 Favorite Getaway Spas in the World by SpaFinder's 2010 Readers' Choice Awards. For a debriefing on local Lahaina legends, visit Pu'uhonua O Nanea cultural center. Eat at Mauka Makai, lounge by a rejuvenating pool with island platforms or work out in our WestinWORKOUT Fitness Studio. Our beach resort even offers ukulele lessons, hula dances and Kona lobster straight from the fisherman's cage. When the sun sets behind the palms, sink into your Heavenly Bed. Our all-villa resort rentals feature marble bathrooms, room service and beach views. Refresh, refuel and relax on your Lahai

name: NEW Guesthouse-Full Kit & Bath w/ Ocean Views!
neighborhood_overview:
The neighborhood is on agricultural land, and is somewhat removed from the hustle and bustle of city life. There are no street lights, and the roads can be bumpy (it's located on a volcano).
Situated at 3600' elevation (in the clouds), in the largest subdivision in the world on the slopes of the largest Volcano (Mauna Loa) in the world!

Located 1.25 hours from Kona and 1.75 hours from Hilo Hawaii.

There are no sidewalks or streetlights, and given the elevation it is not recommended to stray too far from the home on foot.
host_about:
Born and Raised in Indiana, where we're known for 'Hoosier Hospitality.'  As a 5 star rated Turo Powerhost, we have experience hosting guests. 

If our home is available you'll find it priced BELOW average prices on the island.  The drive to our unit puts you in the middle of so many Hawaii Island attractions without the heat and congestion you'll find in Kona/Hilo.  

Reach out with any questions, E Komo Mai to Hawaii Island!

name: Island Bliss: Relax in Paradise
neighborhood_overview:
Welcome to Molokai, The Most Hawaiian Island, where the aloha spirit flourishes and nature takes center stage. With vast expanses of empty beaches, miles of hiking trails, and open spaces, Molokai is a true paradise for nature lovers. You won't find any buildings taller than a palm tree here, and ALOHA is not just a word, it's a way of life.

One of the longest white sand beaches in Hawaii can be found here, and you might just have it all to yourself. There's so little automobile traffic that there's not a single traffic light. No malls, no elevators, and no neon. Burger wars? Not here.

Shop in small, friendly businesses in Kaunakakai, the largest town, and in the villages of Kualapuu and Kumu, where local markets offer fresh produce and homemade goods. Life here is slow and relaxed, rural and peaceful. It's like stepping back in time 50 years. Come experience the magic of Molokai, a place like no other.
host_about: Aloha and welcome to the paradise!

name: Epic Hawaiian Memory to Become!
host_about: I have been a real estate agent since 2015. I enjoy living in Hawaii so much! Making my guests feel comfortable in a convenient location during their vacation is very rewarding to me.

name: Lagoon Tower by Hilton - 2BR Suite
neighborhood_overview: Put a Hawaii beach break on your itinerary courtesy of Lagoon Tower, a Hilton Grand Vacations Club, one of the best places to stay in Waikiki. This towering Oahu timeshare resort overlooks world-famous Waikiki Beach and a fish-filled lagoon where you can rent canoes, kayaks and paddleboards to enjoy under the Hawaiian sun. When it comes to family-friendly amenities, Lagoon Tower far from disappoints. Staying here means enjoying Hilton Hawaiian Village’s four swimming pools, a saltwater recreation lagoon, kids’ activities, beach access, watersports, spa experiences, restaurants and bars, plus the essentials for extended stays, including laundry facilities and a state-of-the-art fitness center.

name: Sunroom Suite at Holualoa House
neighborhood_overview:
Holualoa is a quiet artsy town and area, near many popular attractions, but conveniently tucked away from the hustle and bustle of Kailua-Kona.

Holualoa is best known for her Kona Coffee Heritage and exports, she has attracted artisans, musicians, craftspeople and characters, in large part because of fabulous weather, cool, comfortable sleeping conditions, lush vegetation and convenient location with views to the horizon.

In historic Holualoa town about 4 minutes away, you'll find many art galleries featuring traditional Hawaiian art styles and local artists, 2 coffee shops, and Paul's place convienience store. Not too much farther down the road is an excellent Mom & Pop Mexican lunch spot, Mi Taqueria Potosina!

Along the Mamalahoa Hwy. you are sure to find coffee farms offering Coffee tastings and samples!
host_about: Jacob and I live in the attached home with our cat and 2 roommates. Airbnb has played a major role in my life, my father ran a hostel when I was a teenager until Covid hit, and now I run my own Airbnb with my partner Jacob. Our airbnb was converted from my childhood bedroom, and we hope you will feel as comfy and cozy as I did! I've always lived in Hawaii, worked as a tour guide and park ranger, and am always happy to share my insights with you!

host_about: A tiki is a large or small wooden, pounamu or other stone carving in humanoid form, although this is a somewhat archaic usage in the Māori language. Hei-tiki are often considered taonga, especially if they are older and have been passed down throughout multiple generations. Carvings are often served to mark the boundaries of sacred or significant sites.   We hope to share our heritage & love for our sacred site with you at this retreat.

name: Mountain View Retreat Unit 2

Private Home Near VNP - Nature Views & Tranquility
neighborhood_overview:
Nestled in the heart of Volcano Village, our Rainforest Retreat offers an enchanting escape just moments away from some of the Big Island's most spectacular sights. This charming community sits at the edge of the Volcano National Park, allowing for easy exploration of its stunning volcanic landscapes and lush rainforests. Discover the local art scene, with galleries and studios dotting the area, showcasing the work of the island's talented artisans.

Just a short stroll from your door, the village offers cozy cafes, delightful restaurants, and quaint shops, providing all the comforts and conveniences you might desire. For outdoor enthusiasts, nearby trails invite you to wander through native forests, experience the thrill of seeing an active volcano, or simply enjoy the tranquility of the island's natural beauty.
host_about:
Aloha, I'm originally from Kailua, Hawaii, and spend time between both Oahu and BI. 

Volcano Village holds a special place in my heart. It's where my family has had a home for as long as I can remember, a place where I've spent countless hours as a kid exploring every nook and cranny of the rainforest and learning to appreciate the quiet moments.

Looking forward to sharing my home with you and hoping it becomes a part of your own Hawaii story.

host_about: Hawaii is a unique place and worth understanding on its own terms. A Hawaiian-language speaker, I'm a geographer specializing in Hawai'i and Pacific Islands.  I worked at the Smithsonian National Museum of the American Indian for 12 years and now run two cultural-education non-profits: the Pacific Worlds Institute and Nā Aikāne o Pu'ukohola.  I'm very happy to share information about this island and can provide private tours if desired.

neighborhood_overview:
Kuhio Village is an apartment complex located in the Waikiki area of Honolulu, Hawaii. This neighborhood is known for its vibrant atmosphere, beautiful beaches, and a mix of both residential and tourist-related establishments. Here's a brief neighborhood description of Kuhio Village:

Beach Proximity: Kuhio Village is just a short walk away from the world-famous Waikiki Beach. Residents and visitors can easily access the golden sands and clear waters of this iconic beach.

Tourist Hub: Waikiki is a popular tourist destination, and Kuhio Village is no exception. It is home to numerous hotels, resorts, restaurants, and shops that cater to tourists from around the world.

Dining and Entertainment: The neighborhood offers a wide range of dining options, from local Hawaiian cuisine to international flavors. You can find everything from casual beachside cafes to upscale dining establishments. There are also plenty of bars and clubs for nightlife entertainment.

name: Aloha! Hawaii. Walk to the beach
neighborhood_overview:
Welcome to Molokai, The Most Hawaiian Island, where the aloha spirit flourishes and nature takes center stage. With vast expanses of empty beaches, miles of hiking trails, and open spaces, Molokai is a true paradise for nature lovers. You won't find any buildings taller than a palm tree here, and ALOHA is not just a word, it's a way of life.

One of the longest white sand beaches in Hawaii can be found here, and you might just have it all to yourself. There's so little automobile traffic that there's not a single traffic light. No malls, no elevators, and no neon. Burger wars? Not here.

Shop in small, friendly businesses in Kaunakakai, the largest town, and in the villages of Kualapuu and Kumu, where local markets offer fresh produce and homemade goods. Life here is slow and relaxed, rural and peaceful. It's like stepping back in time 50 years. Come experience the magic of Molokai, a place like no other.
host_about: Aloha and welcome to the paradise!

name: Oceanview Moloka'i Studio
Camp Ku'uipo
neighborhood_overview: Hawaiian Ocean View Estates is America's largest planned urban development with over 10,000 one acre parcels. It's very sparsely populated with less than 5,000 residents. Most of the land is raw lava rock and indigenous 'ohi'a trees found nowhere else on earth. Feral goats patrol the slopes while the i'o or the indigenous Hawaiian hawk and the pueo or indigenous Hawaiian owl patrol the skies. The roads are in good shape and easy to get around on but they extend for miles so a car is absolutely necessary for getting around.
host_about:

Kumu Hale Guest Rooms
Cozy Studio: King Size Bed; Volcanoes Park.
Cozy unit with A/C
The Aloha Place
neighborhood_overview:
The neighborhood is country style Hawai'i. Preserved Hawai'i, that is unincorporated. Neighbors are friendly though they appreciate their privacy and not to be disturbed by tourism. Lay low and enjoy the Hawai'i lifestyle here.
Around 7:00 am you might hear the chickens from surrounding neighbors. I don't own any chickens so it is quite peaceful. My place is hugged by 2600 acres of Hawai'i state land. We are on our own little corner of the island. The Hawaiians valued the sense of seclusion and an abundance in space. The homes here are built with that tradition of "not being able to see another person's house in your view. This is why in this area things are so "far away" than what you may be use to living on a mainland country. A new perspective to absorb!
host_about:
Aloha, I’m Linda. I travel the world for fun. I am grateful for the Airbnb community and all its kind hosts that have made seeing the world more affordable, comfortable, and safe. 
And how I have been able to open my home to world travelers and share the love for the island of Hawai’i. I value seeing the world in an unincorporated way and truly feeling connected to the cultural energy every place gives us. 

I’m a friendly chipper person who loves to garden, yoga, ocean, and live a healthy fulfilling life.

name: Countryside Oahu, Warm Showers & Walk to Beach
host_about: After I graduated college, I went on a road trip from Virginia to California in my minivan with my dog. I loved it so much that I wanted people to have a similar experience here on the islands. I decided to turn it into a little business and rent out 3 vans for camping lovers like myself! I now manage three glamping tents as well. As you can see, I enjoy the outdoors and I hope you get to enjoy the island the best way possible, by being outdoors!

name: Cute Condo in Waikiki #207
Great place in Waikiki!
Bamboo Jungle Cottage Near Ocean ~ Honu
neighborhood_overview:
Welcome to your dream getaway along the famous "Red Road". In paradise our secluded jungle location offers an unforgettable experience, just 2 miles from the renowned black sand beach (Kehena).

Immerse yourself in the vibrant local culture by exploring the Kaimu Farmer's market on Saturday mornings, a mere 5 miles away. Indulge in the eclectic offerings of artisan vendors, delectable prepared food, and fresh produce at the lively Maku'u market on Sunday mornings, conveniently located just 10 miles from your haven. Don't forget a visit to Uncle Robert's. A local gathering place for food music and traditional Awa (kava) since 1962. Try to get there Wednesday evenings for live music.

For a fascinating journey into nature's artistry, take a scenic 30-minute drive to the Lava Tree State Monument. Marvel at the captivating lava molds left behind by the historic 1790 flow—a testament to the raw power of the island's volcanic history. Don't forget to carve out time for

name: 10min 2 North Shore,Central Oahu
neighborhood_overview: Wahiawa a little town in the middle of Oahu with agricultural history.  It could be seen as “country” or a bit “gritty” and this property is smack right in the middle of it all, being on the busiest intersection of our town - so road noise is a consideration. We are just a few minutes(less than a mile to Wheeler Airfield and Schofield Barracks.  Wahiawa General Hospital is also. Few blocks away. Wahiawa also offers itself as an affordable alternative to the North Shore, just a 10-15 minutes coast down the hill to Historic Haleiwa town “the gateway to North Shore”.  Yet,much more convenient - accessible to shopping/marketing conveniences, health care, eateries and Costco.

name: Camp Ohana
neighborhood_overview: Hawaiian Ocean View Estates is America's largest planned urban development with over 10,000 one acre parcels. It's very sparsely populated with less than 5,000 residents. Most of the land is raw lava rock and indigenous 'ohi'a trees found nowhere else on earth. Feral goats patrol the slopes while the i'o or the indigenous Hawaiian hawk and the pueo or indigenous Hawaiian owl patrol the skies. The roads are in good shape and easy to get around on but they extend for miles so a car is absolutely necessary for getting around.

host_about: I love plants, and have 2 green thumbs.  I learned permaculture by trial and error on my land, and over 25 years have an ongoing creation that is truly my grand canvas, my life painting on my Hawaii property- Pua Mana.  Over the years I have learned to create beauty with growing things, and my love of color comes to life in the flowers that I propagate. As an avid Beekeeper, I tend my beehives and harvest amazing honey, specializing in Treatment-Free Beekeeping in Top Bar Hives.  Currently living in the Rogue Valley in S. Oregon and growing very different flowers and veggies on the property that I rent.  I am a Fiber Artist that creates wearable art with natural dyes, silk and printed with leaves.  I am passionate about creating art with nature in this way as well as my gardens! The change in surroundings to a temperate climate after 20 years in the tropics is quite enjoyable.  I spend as much time in the winter at Pua Mana as my schedule permits, always with the longing to be floating in the deep blue ocean waters of Kapoho, drinking green coconuts and eating my giant papayas.

name: Marriott’s Kaua‘i Beach Club - 2BR Oceanview Villa
neighborhood_overview: Plan your island getaway to Marriott's Kaua'i Beach Club. Within steps of Kalapaki Beach, our condo offers unforgettable oceanfront living in Lihue. Relax with signature resort amenities, a gourmet center for preparing meals and ocean and garden views. Refresh in the 26,000-square-foot outdoor pool, soothe sore muscles in one of the whirlpool spas or watch the kids frolic in the children's pool. Work out in the fitness center and enjoy numerous family activities and recreation throughout Kauai, including scuba outings, surfing and snorkeling. name: New Listing | Maui Oasis at The Grand Champions
host_about:
Matthew exemplifies integrity, energy, hard work, and service in every detail of your real estate transaction. Matthew grew up in West Springfield, Massachusetts and is a first generation Portuguese American. An 18 year island resident, Matthew began his real estate career in Hawaii and has established his reputation for building relationships with his clientele along with his commitment to community service as avid volunteer with the Special Olympics. 

“A defining moment in my life was my first year as a volunteer in the Special Olympics. It was then that I realized that life is about paying it forward. I saw first-hand how influencing others could help bring the best results to unlocking people’s limitations to reach their full potential.” 

A family man who enjoys spoiling his two God children, Matthew is also an athlete by nature and sports enthusiast. In his downtime, you’ll find him enjoying the perks of island living; hiking, kayaking, stand up paddle boarding, golfing, quality time with friends and family. Even though he has settled thousands of miles away from his home town, you will still catch him cheering on his beloved Boston Celtics, Boston Bruins, Boston Red Sox and the New England Patriots. 

Matthew has built a solid foundation of successfully guiding local, national and multi-national clients with their real estate acquisitions on Maui. He specializes in applying his expertise and market knowledge to each transaction. Matthew’s portfolio of high-end residential sales include over $24 million dollars in career sales. 

Matthew flies the country to build strong relationships with his clientele and uses his experience and foresight to proactively address details before they become a problem. He works diligently for his clients and initiates communication in every detail of the transaction, from the first phone call all the way to close. 

Matthew displays the “Aloha Spirit” daily with his volunteer work, business and in life itself.

Aloha,

name: Marriott’s Kaua‘i Beach Club - 1BR Oceanview Villa
neighborhood_overview: Plan your island getaway to Marriott's Kaua'i Beach Club. Within steps of Kalapaki Beach, our condo offers unforgettable oceanfront living in Lihue. Relax with signature resort amenities, a gourmet center for preparing meals and ocean and garden views. Refresh in the 26,000-square-foot outdoor pool, soothe sore muscles in one of the whirlpool spas or watch the kids frolic in the children's pool. Work out in the fitness center and enjoy numerous family activities and recreation throughout Kauai, including scuba outings, surfing and snorkeling. After a full day of Kauai sun, sand and surf, pamper yourself at the tranquil day spa or indulge at one of the beachfront restaurants before retiring to your room. It's all waiting for you at our oceanfront resort in Kauai. This vacation club resort shares grounds with The Royal Sonesta Kaua'i Resort.

name: Rare Corner Modern Waikiki Studio Oasis 14F
host_about: Aloha! I’m Charlie, the proud owner and your host at Hawaii Home Properties LLC. Having embraced the beautiful islands of Hawaii as my home for many years, I've come to not only understand but also live and breathe the true essence of the Aloha spirit.  Whether you're here to bask in the serene beaches, explore the lush landscapes, or simply unwind in the comfort of our homes, I'm here to make your Hawaiian getaway seamless and extraordinary.

name: Seaview Retreat
host_about: Aloha! I traveled to Hawaii in 2015 and fell in love with the natural and raw beauty of Kalapana on the south east coast of the Hawai’i island.  I moved here in 2018 shortly after the big lava flow that took part of the Leilani subdivision. I was tired of the busy and noisy city life and I wanted to try living a much simpler life closer to nature.

name: Hilo Red Ti cottage
neighborhood_overview:
Minutes from various beaches! Easy access to swimming, fishing, snorkeling, boating, surfing, paddle boarding, hiking, Volcanoes National Park, waterfalls, restaurants and more.
Nearest commercial Airport: Hilo international Airport is 13 miles away.
host_about: Aloha, my name is Maggie. I am a Big Island resident living in Hilo with my family. I love to host members of the airbnb community and those visiting our island home, it's a pleasure! I strive to provide outstanding experiences to my guests with with simple, clean, beautiful accommodations and clear communication. I am always excited to share my knowledge of the East side of the island with visitors. I look forward to meeting you!

name: Fairy Cottage Oceanview Glamping
The Westin Nanea Ocean Villas - 2BR Villa
neighborhood_overview: Thrive on Hawaii's second largest island. The Westin Nanea Ocean Villas, Ka'anapali is a lively vacation ownership beach resort located in Lahaina, once the royal capital of Maui Loa. Balance historic museum tours with rain forest hikes to 400-foot waterfalls. Peer down a dormant volcano or snorkel The Forbidden Coast for unspoiled coral reefs. On your return, visit our sister property's Spa Helani, voted Top 10 Favorite Getaway Spas in the World by SpaFinder's 2010 Readers' Choice Awards. For a debriefing on local Lahaina legends, visit Pu'uhonua O Nanea cultural center. Eat at Mauka Makai, lounge by a rejuvenating pool with island platforms or work out in our WestinWORKOUT Fitness Studio. Our beach resort even offers ukulele lessons, hula dances and Kona lobster straight from the fisherman's cage. When the sun sets behind the palms, sink into your Heavenly Bed. Our all-villa resort rentals feature marble bathrooms, room service and beach views. Refresh, refuel and relax on your Lahai

name: 101A Date St Single Rm 1 bed
Spacious Room
host_about:
Aloha, 
My name is Cynthia. I’ve been on the islands for over 9 years, and I couldn’t be happier. I'm ordained, so if you’re looking to get married on the island, I can assist you, I also run my own aesthetician business at my home office, so if you’re interesting in getting pampered during your stay…. feel free to reach out, and I am also a paralegal. I'm into photography as my top hobby. Oh, and the ocean brings me peace and tranquility.

name: Coastal Haven: Chic Studio with Parking in Waikiki
neighborhood_overview: The condo is located in the heart of Waikiki, a short walk from the beach. It is safe and well lit, with the newly built International Market Place less than 200 yards away. There's a foodcourt. There are also a few grocery and convenience stores nearby for quick supply runs.
host_about: Aloha, My name is Avery. Grew up in Hawaii and a few other places around the pacific but Hawaii will always be dear to me. I speak Mandarin Chinese and English. Happy to help the would be traveler when you come to Honolulu!

name: Spacious 1 Bed w/ AC, Parking, Pool Near Ala Moana
neighborhood_overview: Discover the enchantment of Ala Moana and just minutes away from Waikiki. A paradise where the beaches beckon with golden sands, the shopping and dining options are limitless, and endless activities throughout the day and night . Here, every moment is an invitation to relax, celebrate, and create unforgettable memories—all within arm's reach. Yet, the magic doesn't end at Waikiki's shores. Venture just a short drive away to explore the world-class Ala Moana Shopping Center, the iconic North Shore, and the diverse beauty of Oahu. Embark on this journey to immerse yourself in Hawaii's rich culture and breathtaking landscapes. Waikiki is not just a destination; it's the beginning of your extraordinary adventure.
host_about: Experience paradise and the beauty of Hawaii through Happy Vacations. We managed short-term rental properties on the island of Oahu. License RB-21552.

name: Aloha by the Sea in Waikiki, Chic, Stylish & NEW!
Bamboo Jungle Cottage Near Ocean ~ Shaka
neighborhood_overview:
Welcome to your dream getaway along the famous "Red Road". In paradise our secluded jungle location offers an unforgettable experience, just 2 miles from the renowned black sand beach (Kehena).

Immerse yourself in the vibrant local culture by exploring the Kaimu Farmer's market on Saturday mornings, a mere 5 miles away. Indulge in the eclectic offerings of artisan vendors, delectable prepared food, and fresh produce at the lively Maku'u market on Sunday mornings, conveniently located just 10 miles from your haven. Don't forget a visit to Uncle Robert's. A local gathering place for food music and traditional Awa (kava) since 1962. Try to get there Wednesday evenings for live music.

For a fascinating journey into nature's artistry, take a scenic 30-minute drive to the Lava Tree State Monument. Marvel at the captivating lava molds left behind by the historic 1790 flow—a testament to the raw power of the island's volcanic history. Don't forget to carve out time for

name: The Westin Princeville Ocean Resort - 2BR Villa
neighborhood_overview:
Discover The Westin Princeville Ocean Resort Villas on North Shore Kauai. Situated on the cliffside overlooking the Pacific, this family-friendly vacation ownership resort is near Anini Beach and a short drive from picturesque Hanalei Bay. Explore The Wai`oli Mission and splendid 1,000-acre Limahuli Garden. Unwind and refuel after your adventures at Princeville Bistro or Nanea Bar & Grill restaurant. After you experience the North Shore activities, energize at the 24-hour WestinWORKOUT® Fitness Studio or swim in one of the sparkling outdoor pools overlooking the ocean at Princeville oceanfront resort. Embrace pure tranquility with a soothing massage in an open-air cabana. Renew your body and soul at The Westin Princeville Ocean Resort Villas.

Please note that accessing the beach from the resort involves navigating through a cliffside terrain.

NEARBY BEACHES:

- Anini Beach: Approximately 10 minutes
- Hideaways Beach: Approximately 5 minutes
- H

host_about: I am a traveler at heart who is highly motivated, active and inspired by people, places and most importantly, nature! Waikiki Shell (Concert Hall)

Kapiolani Park (Great place to picnic, walk, jogging, yoga etc..)
Starbucks/Jamaba Juice Coffee Bean/Bogurts (More coffee Shops)

My pass times include socializing, shopping, home improvement projects, all types of athletics especially distance running, Mt. Biking, Basketball, and hiking.  However, nothing feels better than an spending time with my incredible two kids, wife, and amazing parents!

name: The Westin Princeville Ocean Resort - 1BR Villa
neighborhood_overview:
Discover The Westin Princeville Ocean Resort Villas on North Shore Kauai. Situated on the cliffside overlooking the Pacific, this family-friendly vacation ownership resort is near Anini Beach and a short drive from picturesque Hanalei Bay. Explore The Wai`oli Mission and splendid 1,000-acre Limahuli Garden. Unwind and refuel after your adventures at Princeville Bistro or Nanea Bar & Grill restaurant. After you experience the North Shore activities, energize at the 24-hour WestinWORKOUT® Fitness Studio or swim in one of the sparkling outdoor pools overlooking the ocean at Princeville oceanfront resort. Embrace pure tranquility with a soothing massage in an open-air cabana. Renew your body and soul at The Westin Princeville Ocean Resort Villas.

Please note that accessing the beach from the resort involves navigating through a cliffside terrain.

NEARBY BEACHES:

- Anini Beach: Approximately 10 minutes
- Hideaways Beach: Approximately 5 minutes
- H

neighborhood_overview: Embrace a welcoming abundance of amenities at The Westin Ka'anapali Ocean Resort Villas. While you can enjoy Ka'anapali's famed whale-watching, snorkeling, sailing, windsurfing and scuba-diving just steps away, there are plenty of diversions at our beachfront vacation ownership resort to keep the entire family entertained. There are Westin touches that keep in harmony with Ka'anapali's rich culture. Enjoy two sparkling oceanfront refreshing pools with rock waterfalls and soothing whirlpool spas, three restaurants at the resort, and two on-site markets providing a range of sundries, snacks, and supplies. Outdoor gas grills are perfectly situated for sunset barbeques.

As a true island enthusiast, I am passionate about sharing the love and beauty of Hawaii with others.

name: The Westin Nanea Ocean - 2BR Oceanfront Villa!
neighborhood_overview: Thrive on Hawaii's second largest island. The Westin Nanea Ocean Villas, Ka'anapali is a lively vacation ownership beach resort located in Lahaina, once the royal capital of Maui Loa. Balance historic museum tours with rain forest hikes to 400-foot waterfalls. Peer down a dormant volcano or snorkel The Forbidden Coast for unspoiled coral reefs. On your return, visit our sister property's Spa Helani, voted Top 10 Favorite Getaway Spas in the World by SpaFinder's 2010 Readers' Choice Awards. For a debriefing on local Lahaina legends, visit Pu'uhonua O Nanea cultural center. Eat at Mauka Makai, lounge by a rejuvenating pool with island platforms or work out in our WestinWORKOUT Fitness Studio. Our beach resort even offers ukulele lessons, hula dances and Kona lobster straight from the fisherman's cage. When the sun sets behind the palms, sink into your Heavenly Bed. Our all-villa resort rentals feature marble bathrooms, room service and beach views. Refresh, refuel and relax on your Lahai

name: Nalehua Rustic Cabin
neighborhood_overview: Quiet, private, and secluded. When in the cabin it feels like no one is around. This property is on three acres at 3000 feet elevation. The temperatures are cooler which allows for less bugs and no ants. The property has a private gated entry leading into the sanctuary. This is a dreamy place on the Big Island.

host_about: Not only are we parents who came to Hawaii to pursue our goals of living 100% off the grid and supplying our own food, we are avid Permaculture/Biodynamic plant people who love sharing our knowledge about gardening with others. We offer workshops, tours and want to make your stay as enjoyable as we can. We help guide you to a magical experience while in Hawaii. We may even have a bunch of tricks to try in your garden at home!

name: Hualalai Terrace
neighborhood_overview: Our neighborhood is on the slopes of Hualalai, one of the 5 volcanos that constitute Hawaii Island. It is a quiet, well-established residential area.
host_about:
I'm a Silicon Valley professional having the time of my life building my startup.  My daughter, Aurora, manages our location in Santa Clara. She works nearly full time and is attending college.  My husband, Bill and I, love playing golf, snorkeling in Hawaii and going for a drive on the coast with the top down on our Mustang.
I've lived in Silicon Valley nearly all my life and I enjoy making our place home to guests whether they are with us for a day or for multiple years.
I have a commitment to people and am out to have everyone recognize and express their brilliance in the world for the well being of humanity and our world.

name: Sanoe
Big Island Cozy Sanctuary
host_about:
Hi Airbnb,

Some of our favorite places to travel:  Greece, London, the Big Island of Hawaii, and the Cinque Terre (Italy).  But any place that opens our eyes to new things is great.  

We share our time between San Francisco and the Big Island. Jon works in solar energy and Fahmida in neuropsychology. 

We are both from the Midwest, primarily reside in San Francisco and were married on the Big Island. We purchased our first home on the Big Island because it is a special place for us. 

As hosts we want share the aloha spirit and the sanctuary of our peaceful retreat with you. 

Hope to be traveling in your neck of the woods soon or sharing our part of the woods with you. 

Fahmida & Jon

neighborhood_overview:
Marriott’s Maui Ocean Club is one of the most popular timeshare resorts - and for good reason! This spectacular 16 acre Kaanapali Beachfront resort resort occupies one of the most coveted locales in Lahaina and also boasts a number of delicious restaurants, poolside dining options, fitness center and on-site tennis courts. For the ultimate in relaxation, book a session at the resort's tranquil day spa, which includes outdoor spa cabanas. And of course, there's the sprawling 3.5 acre Superpool, showcasing dazzling waterfalls, grottos and waterways, a Shipwreck Beach and Waterslide for children and a pool bar.

Marriott’s Maui Ocean Club includes the Molokai, Maui and Lanai Towers, offering studio, one-bedroom and two-bedroom accommodations. One-bedroom and two-bedroom suites feature a lavish master bedroom with an in-suite bathroom and a balcony.
